title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix, egg and water.
Spread on lightly greased pizza pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: baked cheese
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add sour cream, onion, bacon and cheese. Spoon in enough mayonnaise for good consistency (not more than 3/4 cup).

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add enough water to reserved fruit juices to make 1 1/2 cups and mix with gelatin.
Stir in blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into a 1-quart dish and chill until firm.
Blend cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla. Spread over congealed salad and sprinkle with pecans.

title: spoon bread
directions: Bring cornmeal, shortening and 2 cans of milk to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Combine egg, remaining milk and salt and add to the mixture.
Quickly stir in baking powder.
Pour mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until top is golden brown. Serves 12.

title: southfork "chili"
directions: Brown ground beef and pour off fat.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic, red pepper, chili powder, cumin, oregano and salt.
Mix well.
Cook until onion and green pepper become tender.
Add beans, tomatoes, corn and tomato sauce.
Stir to mix well, breaking up tomatoes with a fork.
Simmer slowly, stirring occasionally, until thickened and blended (about 45 minutes).

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt butter, food coloring, marshmallows and vanilla in a double boiler.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Mix well.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cut brown off bread and line a greased 13 x 9-inch pan with bread.
Put sausage on top of bread, then cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over other mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: baked broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter; add rice, undiluted soups and cheese.
Mix together; turn into buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add broccoli and stir.
Bake in 350° oven 20 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: nutty slaw
directions: In a large bowl combine ingredients and mix well.
Chill for 3 hours or more before serving.
This colorful slaw is a perfect addition to any meal.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Stir cracker crumbs, margarine and nuts together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan (all except 1/2 cup).
Mix instant pudding and milk together and add to this, the ice cream.
Mix well.
Pour over cracker crumb crust.
Top with
a large Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on this and refrigerate.
Do not freeze.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in their skins.
Cool, peel and shred coarsely. Put cheese and 1/4 cup butter in pan over low heat and stir until cheese melts.
Take from heat and add the sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Stir.
Fold the potatoes into the cheese mixture. Spoon the potato-cheese mixture into a 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Combine noodles, tuna, soup, cheese, milk and olives (if desired).
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and bake according to box directions.
Cool and mix together last 3 ingredients and frost cake.
Cover and freeze overnight.
Remove and keep cake refrigerated.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef with onions.
Add taco seasoning.
Spread beans in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Spoon meat mixture over beans.
Spread salsa on top.
Top with shredded cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: oatmeal raisin cookie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla on medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease small or large pans. Fill pans 1/2 full.
Bake at 350°.
Check after 45 minutes by inserting toothpick in center.
They will be done when toothpick comes out dry with no moist batter.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on bottom of a lightly-greased cookie sheet.
Bake and cool as directed on package.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry Hidden Valley mix.
Spread on cooled crescent rolls.
Sprinkle broccoli, then cauliflower, then carrots on top of cheese mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut over bottom of pan. Make cake mix per directions on box.
Pour batter over pecans and coconut.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together and chill for salad or dessert.

title: crisp puff-pastry sticks
directions: Remove puff-pastry from package and thaw at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
On lightly floured surface, unfold 1 sheet of puff pastry.
With floured rolling pin, roll pastry into 18 x 10-inch rectangle.
In cup with fork, beat egg, salt and 1 teaspoon water.
Brush pastry with some egg mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Cut pastry sheet crosswise into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Place on ungreased large baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden.
Remove.
Repeat with second sheet only.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 12 dozen strips.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Toast 1/2 cup coconut.
Set aside. Bake shell 8 minutes.
Cool slightly.
In medium bowl, beat eggs. Add remaining ingredients except coconut.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with toasted coconut. Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes longer or until done.
Cool or chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: strawberry-banana shake
directions: Add all the ingredients to a container.
Chop or mince ingredients together.
Mix and enjoy.

title: bollos
directions: Soak peas overnight. Remove the husks by rubbing between hands until they are loose. Place peas in water again and the husks will rise to the top. Pour them off. Grind peas, garlic and peppers to a very fine paste. Save drippings from grinder and add along with the salt. Add a little water if necessary. Beat the mixture with electric beater until it becomes creamy. Drop by the spoonful into hot deep fat and fry until brown (just as you would hush puppies).

title: pear salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add cream cheese until melted. Mix with a mixer.
Add Cool Whip.
Add pears, juice from pears and nuts.
Chill.

title: cream puffs
directions: Sift flour and measure; add salt and sift again.
Combine shortening and boiling water in small saucepan.
Keep over low heat until shortening is melted.
Add flour all at one time and stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball and leaves side of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition either by hand or electric mixer.
Continue beating until a thick dough is formed. Dough should be shiny.
Drop by tablespoon or heaping teaspoonful onto a greased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for about 50 minutes or until beads of moisture no longer appear on surface; do not open oven door during early part of baking.
When cool, slit sides and fill with Cream Filling. Sprinkle tops with powdered sugar.

title: date crisp
directions: Combine sugar, milk, egg, flour, salt and baking powder; beat well.
Add nuts and dates.
Spread batter in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place wings in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Combine remaining ingredients and brush generously over wings.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, basting frequently.
Serve with Chinese hot mustard, if desired.

title: brown sugar crisp
directions: Cook
condensed
milk
and brown sugar in top of double boiler over
boiling water until thick.
Remove from heat and add
corn flakes,
mixing
thoroughly.
Drop
from spoon onto buttered cookie
sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Mix first three ingredients in a separate bowl.
Mix parsley and onion.
In a 2 to 3-quart casserole put a layer of bread crumb mixture, then layer of parsley and onions.
Next put a layer of oysters with 1 drop of Tabasco sauce, salt and butter on each oyster.
Repeat procedure until all is in baking dish.
End with crumb mixture.
When you have completed layers gently pour wine and then cream over layers.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: marinated potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
When cool enough to handle, peel and cut into chunks.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix milk and eggs with the mashed bananas.
Sift the dry ingredients into the banana mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian turkey casserole
directions: Starting with a cold nonstick frying pan, brown turkey meat slowly or brown in a microwave oven. Drain off any fat.
Add the onion and garlic.
Saute in 1 teaspoon liquid Butter Buds. Add turkey meat back to skillet and cook about 1 or 2 more minutes. Stir in spices and tomato sauce and heat until thick and bubbling.

title: frito salad
directions: Melt cheese in milk over very low heat or in a double boiler. Keep warm.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes, onions, avocado and Tabasco sauce.
Season with pepper and garlic salt.
Add Fritos.
Toss well.
Pour melted cheese mixture over salad.
Toss and serve.

title: chicken or tuna casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spring strawberry salad(makes 4 servings)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and stir well with a whisk. Combine greens and strawberries in a large bowl. Add vinegar mixture. Toss to coat. Sprinkle with pine nuts (if desired).

title: microwave chicken with herbs
directions: Spray all sides of chicken with Kitchen Bouquet microwave browning spray (about 12 sprays).
Brush with herb butter.
Place, skin side down, in microwave usable baking dish.
Cover loosely with wax paper and microwave (High) 10 minutes.
Turn skin side up.
Spray with Kitchen Bouquet microwave browning spray (about 6 sprays).
Brush with herb butter.
Microwave (High) 10 minutes or until leg moves freely and inner thigh meat is done.
Garnish with fresh herbs, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; fold in nuts, strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture in pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream.
Gently spoon in strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate several hours, or overnight.
Cut into squares; serve on lettuce.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening.
Beat into this mixture sugar and eggs, adding each egg, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt.
To this mixture, add milk and vanilla.
Combine the flour mixture, milk and vanilla mixture alternately, beginning with the flour mixture.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: peach jam
directions: Set timer for 1 minute cooking.
Place peaches and Sure-Jell in a large 6 to 8-quart heavy cooker.
Bring quickly to a hard boil, stirring constantly.
At once, add sugar (can't be stirred down). Boil hard 1 more minute.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam with metal spoon.
May freeze or place in clean jars and seal.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a small bowl, combine stuffing and oleo.
Reserve 1/2 cup stuffing mixture.
In a 2-quart baking dish, spread remaining stuffing mixture.
In bowl, combine soup, sour cream and cheese. Stir in squash and carrot.
Spread soup mixture over stuffing mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: prince edward island bannock
directions: Try 3/4 cup milk and add, if needed, to roll out mixture. Strike down with butcher knife to look like biscuits.
Grease pan and bake at 400° approximately 30 minutes until brown.

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: Mix all ingredients; let marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours, stirring often.
Serve on toast squares or crackers.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces, wash and pat dry with paper towels.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, pepper and paprika. Dip pieces of chicken in cream, then coat as thickly as possible with seasoned flour.
Preheat skillet to 325° with oil about 5 minutes.
Arrange coated chicken in skillet.
Brown on all sides about 10 minutes.
Cover and cook about 30 minutes on 225°. Remove cover and fry an additional 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pizzelle
directions: Mix well using 1 teaspoon on each iron. Dust with powdered sugar while warm.

title: cinnamon cucumber rings
directions: Put rings in 8 1/2 quarts water and 2 cups lime.
Let stand in lime water for 24 hours.
Drain rings.
Wash in cool water 3 times. Pour clean water over and soak for 3 hours.
Drain, then add 1 cup vinegar, alum and food coloring.
Add enough cold water to cover cucumbers.
Heat and simmer for 24 hours.
Drain and rinse with cool water.

title: kraut-swiss-rye casserole
directions: Mix together kraut, onion and sour cream. Place mixture into 9x13 baking dish. Spread the swiss cheese over the mixture and top it with the crumbled rye bread. Pour the melted margarine over the casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: bayley's west indies salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and marinate for 2 to 12 hours.

title: strawberries accent dessert
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, nuts and melted butter or margarine.
Spread evenly in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Sprinkle 2/3 of crumbs in 13 x 9-inch glass dish.

title: korean beef
directions: Tenderize meat on both sides with wooden meat mallet. Partially freeze meat and slice paper thin.

title: reuben rolls
directions: Blend corn beef, cheese and sauerkraut together.
Add Miracle Whip and mustard.
Roll out pizza dough and spread mixture all over.
Roll dough up and bake on cookie sheet at 425° for 10 minutes or 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken supreme casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Remove from heat and mix with all remaining ingredients except noodles.
Alternate layers of noodles with layers of meat mixture in a greased casserole dish. Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, then add cocoa and cornstarch.
Add milk.
Stir well.
Cook slowly until thickens.
Add 1 tablespoon butter.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add the flavoring.
Pour into already baked pie crust.
Make your meringue with leftover egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 375° until meringue is golden (about 5 minutes).

title: special party dip
directions: Brown ground round; drain.
Cook sausage (crumbled, not patties); drain.
In a crock-pot, put chunks of Velveeta cheese, can of chili, cooked sausage and meat all together.
Cover; cook on low.
Eat with chips or on small deli breads, toasting the little breads with this mixture on top of it.

title: quick fruit dip
directions: Soften cheese in microwave for 1 minute.
Add marshmallow cream.
Mix well.
Serve with sliced fruit.

title: frozen fruit salad ii
directions: Blend cream cheese and salad dressing together; add fruit, marshmallows, pecans and powdered sugar.
Fold in whipped cream very gently.
Pour into mold; freeze just until firm.
Slice and serve on greens.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Separate eggs; beat yolks.
Add grated rind and lemon juice; stir well.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Put in pie crust.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold in 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar. Spread on top of pie.
Place in preheated oven (350° to 375°) for about 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove and cool.
Put in refrigerator for about 24 hours before serving.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Mix together yeast, sugar, salt and water.
Sift a mound of flour, about 4 cups and add to the yeast mixture.
Stir until dough is completely moistened.
Turn mixture on lightly floured board and knead to make soft smooth dough.
Pinch off pieces; roll into ropes and shape into pretzels.

title: old time vinegar pie
directions: Mix flour with half the sugar and add boiling water.
Cook in double boiler for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add rest of sugar and beaten egg yolks; cook a few minutes longer.
Add butter and vinegar.
Flavor with lemon extract (if desired) and cool.
Pour into baked shell and meringue.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, egg, and onion.
Blend with broccoli.
Pour into buttered dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Melt oleo and stuffing crumbs on top of broccoli. Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown rice with oleo; put in a casserole dish and add soup and broth.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole.
Put crushed cornflakes on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve immediately. Serves 8.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out on wax paper.
Use cookie cutters to cut out shapes.
Use toothpick to put hole in top to insert string to hang up.
Move to another sheet of wax paper.
Dry on flat surface until completely dry (about 1 week).
Turn over each day.
When dry, insert gold cord or string for hanging.
Also, can paint designs on ornaments when dry.
Fun to make.

title: peanut butter banana muffins
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and baking powder.
Whisk together milk, peanut butter, banana, egg, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients mixing until moistened.
Fill cups 3/4 full.

title: pam's salad
directions: Bring to boil crushed pineapple just as it comes from can. Remove from heat; add sugar and salt.
Add jello.
Set aside until cools and begins to thicken.
Work in cream cheese that has been standing at room temperature.
Whip cream or canned milk that has been chilled.
It will whip.
Fold into pineapple mixture.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour into good size dish.
Garnish with maraschino cherries (5 or 6).
Refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and cream cheese together.
Add sugar and eggs, beating after each one.
Add flavoring.
Slowly add flour, gradually beating on medium speed.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Drain artichoke hearts, saving juice.
Add onions, pepper, olives and artichoke hearts, all chopped or sliced.
Combine mayonnaise, curry powder and juice from artichoke hearts.
Stir into rice mixture.
Serves 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Pour cherries in bottom of pan.
Drain pineapple.
Pour on top of cherries.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of the cherries and pineapple.
Melt margarine, pour on, then add coconut and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: beverly slimm's beef and mozzarella bake
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef, basil, black pepper and garlic until browned, stirring to separate meat. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soups, water and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Add macaroni.

title: grandma's jack o' lantern pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, pouring mixture into waiting pie crusts.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for about 50 minutes until testing knife comes out clean.
May cook the pumpkin pudding in a baking dish instead.
May serve with whipped cream, chunks of Cheddar cheese or vanilla ice cream.

title: skillet chicken
directions: Shake chicken in paper bag with flour, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
In skillet, brown chicken in Wesson oil. Remove excess fat.
Combine onion, sauce, sugar and vinegar. Pour over chicken. Cook until chicken done.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a saucepan.
Stir well.
Heat slowly over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove cloves and cinnamon sticks before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into pan, pressing evenly, and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Then fill and bake.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all and pour into 2-quart casserole dish, greased with Pam.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: jello-cottage cheese salad
directions: Add together lime and lemon Jell-O to boiling water and stir constantly until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate until firm.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and mix in dry taco seasoning in skillet.
In bowl, mix olives, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and onion.
Drain meat and mix in with salad.
Then break up chips and mix all together.
Top with taco sauce and favorite salad dressing.

title: pasta e fagioli(macaroni and beans)
directions: In hot oil in 5-quart Dutch oven or heavy kettle, saute garlic and onion, stirring, until golden, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, oregano and parsley.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Mash tomatoes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, place one layer cracker crumbs.
Add 1/2 can soup and place sliced boiled eggs on soup. Arrange asparagus and the remaining soup.
Top with cracker crumbs and butter. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: maple balls
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; form into balls.
Melt wax and chocolate over top of a double boiler and keep over heat while dipping balls.
Makes approximately six dozen.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Blend the strawberries, sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and condensed milk together.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Add the milk.
Freeze as usual.

title: crab puffs
directions: Rinse and drain crabmeat.
Mix first 6 ingredients.
Spread on muffins.
Cut each muffin into 6 wedges and place on cookie sheet*.
Broil until golden.

title: picante corn bread
directions: Heat an 8-inch cast-iron skillet at 425° for 5 minutes. Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Make a "well" in the center of the mixture; set aside. Combine buttermilk, eggs and picante sauce.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Remove skillet from oven; add butter.
Pour melted butter into batter.
Blend well and pour mixture into hot skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: creamy frozen salad
directions: Blend sour cream, lemon juice, sugar and salt. Stir in pineapple, cherries, pecans and banana. Pour into 1-quart mold. Cover and freeze. Thaw at room temperature for 15 minutes before serving.

title: large pot brunswick stew
directions: In an iron pot, outside, cook hens and middling meat until half done.
Add hamburger and onions; continue cooking until hens are done.
Add potatoes and cook to pieces, then add tomatoes and butter beans.
Cook stew until well done.
Add corn and butter; cook until corn is done.
Season in the beginning and throughout the cooking.
Cook the stew to desired thickness (approximately 7 hours cooking time).
Serves around 100 people.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour in pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle brown sugar over that.
Pour cake mix on top of that, then add nuts.
Pour melted butter over all.
Cook at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and beat well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Add milk; beat well.
Pour into crust (will make two). Bake until golden brown in 350° oven.

title: dump cake
directions: Spoon cherry pie filling evenly in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon pineapple with juice over pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over pineapple.
Drizzle melted oleo evenly over all. Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake 1 hour in 325° oven or until cake tests done.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Boil water; take from heat and mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13 dish.

title: meat loaf
directions: Saute onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add to ground beef in large bowl.
Sprinkle in salt and pepper; mix well.
Stir in crumbs, eggs and juice.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in a greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 60 to 90 minutes or until browned.
Remove loaf and place on platter.
Serve with brown gravy.

title: cold cookies
directions: Stir together sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil. Remove from heat; immediately add margarine, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until combined.
Add oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Mix and spread in flat pan.
Chill until firm.

title: ten minute tomato soup
directions: Heat tomatoes until boiling.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Return to heat and cook on medium until butter is melted and heated thoroughly.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet and add onion and green pepper. Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes and seasonings, bring to a boil. Stir in rice, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Turn heat off.
Top with slices of Velveeta cheese and cover until melted.

title: bird's nest pie
directions: *Place 1 tablespoon of white vinegar in measuring cup.
Add enough milk to equal 1 cup.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes.
Salt both sides.
Pat into flour, coating well.
Fry in shortening or oil on medium heat until just golden brown on each side.
Lift out with fork and drain on paper towels.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes and onions with water; cook one-half hour until tender.
Add caraway seed, dill weed, milk, salt and pepper. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and butter.

title: green pepper tostadas(health conscious)
directions: Saute green peppers, onion and tomatoes in the oil.
Add the whipped cheese; cook for 5 minutes.
Broil tortillas until slightly crisp.
Place 3 tablespoons of pepper-tomato mixture in the center of each tortilla.
Sprinkle with the grated Mozzarella cheese; broil until the cheese is melted.
Serve topped with shredded lettuce.

title: brownie pudding cake
directions: Sift together flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add milk, oil and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar, remaining cocoa and 1 3/4 cups hot water; pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lucky charm treats
directions: Put butter and marshmallows in big pan on medium heat until melted, then add Lucky Charms cereal and stir.
Spread out in 9 x 13-inch pan that has had butter smeared in it.
That makes it easier to remove from pan.

title: tuna rice bake
directions: Combine rice, 1 slightly beaten egg, butter and parsley. Firmly press mixture against bottom and sides of a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup cheese over rice crust.
Top with half of the tuna; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Beat together milk, 3 eggs, salt and pepper; pour over cheese-tuna mixture.
Sprinkle remaining tuna on top.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter.
Add sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Fold in dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan or 8-inch square cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together.
Make into balls.
Sprinkle with cayenne pepper. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 13 minutes.

title: bacon, eggs and "toast" brunch casserole
directions: Mix together croutons and cheese.
Pour into greased 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients, except bacon, and pour over crouton mixture.
Top with with bacon. Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until eggs set.

title: best rum cake ever!!
directions: Before you start, sample the rum to check for quality.
Good, isn't it?
Now, go ahead, select a large mixing bow, measuring cup, etc.
Check the rum again.
It must be just right.
To be sure rum is of the highest quality, pour 1 level cup of rum into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add meat; cook and brown.
Drain.
Blend in flour and garlic salt.
Gradually add beef broth; stir until thickened.
Stir in sour cream and mushrooms; heat.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: easy way pralines
directions: Combine pudding, brown and granulated sugar and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes.
Candy will be shiny.
Add pecans and stir.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let harden 1 hour.
Makes 24 pralines.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti, onion and celery in broth.
Reserve 1 cup of broth.
Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Top with cheese; bake at 350° until cheese is melted and spaghetti is hot.
This may be frozen without cheese and used later.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Combine morsels and peanut butter in top of double boiler. Place over hot, not boiling, water until melted.
Stir.
Add noodles.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Top with cherry; chill until set.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: hamburger-vegetable soup
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion in a small amount of cooking oil.
When lightly browned, drain off excess fat.
Combine with the remaining ingredients in a large kettle.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes whole in skin until done. Run cold water over the sweet potatoes and remove skin. Break apart sweet potatoes in a bowl. Add butter and mix well with mixer. Stir in sugar, milk, eggs, nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla. Beat on medium speed until mixture is smooth. Pour filling into an unbake pie crust. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes at high speed of electric mixer. Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture and blend well.
Spoon batter onto a greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, spreading evenly to corners. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn cake out onto a towel sprinkled with 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Beginning at narrow end, roll up cake and towel together, jelly roll fashion.
Cool.
Combine 1 cup powdered sugar, cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Unroll cake and spread with filling.
Roll cake up again; chill, seam side down.
When ready to serve, remove from refrigerator and slice.

title: seasoned white beans
directions: Boil
salt
pork
and set aside.
Reserve some of water from pork
to
add
to
beans.
Place beans in pot with water, about 2 to 3-inches above beans.
Boil until beans get to be a little tender; remove beans from fire.
Drain and rinse beans. Into empty pot, add cooking oil and saute onions, celery, bell pepper	and garlic;
add cubed salt pork and smother a little while.
To this,
add	beans
and
some
of
water from pork. Continue cooking
and
adding water until desired creaminess. Add
onion tops
and
parsley.
Should
cook for half hour or more.

title: big bucket in the sky chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Heat oil in a large frying pan. Dip chicken into batter.
Fry chicken in hot oil until cooked and golden brown.

title: pea and rice casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Mix tuna, soup, peas and rice together with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven until edges are browned.

title: heath bars
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with soda crackers (about 35).
Mix butter (oleo) and brown sugar.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Let chips melt.
Spread with a big spoon.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and pat in.
Cut before completely cool.
Refrigerate.

title: texas brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar.
In a saucepan, combine butter, shortening, coffee or water and cocoa. Stir and heat to boiling.
Pour boiling mixture over the flour and sugar in the bowl.
Add the buttermilk, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well.

title: shrimp and lobster bouillabaisse
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, combine tomatoes, broth, clam juice, leeks, water, Cajun seasoning and orange peel.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease and heat a medium iron skillet or 9-inch baking pan.
Combine beaten egg and buttermilk.
Add corn meal; mix sugar and oil.
Stir until moistened.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until brown.

title: raisin, carrot and apple cake
directions: In a bowl, beat the butter, sugar, spices and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients, tossing to blend.
Mixture will be dry. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in 8-inch square pan for 40 to 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: quick pan rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water in a large bowl.
Add sugar, salt, egg, shortening and 1 cup of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour and continue stirring until smooth.
Scrape batter from side of bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled (30 minutes).
Stir batter and turn onto floured surface.
Divide into 12 equal parts.
Shape into smooth ball with lightly greased fingers.
Place in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Let rise until doubled (20 to 30 minutes).
Beat egg white and 1 tablespoon of water slightly and brush over rolls.
Sprinkle with seed.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 12 rolls.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into 3-inch lengths.
Split 1/2 inch up from the stem ends.
Cook in a covered saucepan in an inch of boiling water until tender, 8 to 10 minutes after the water starts to boil.
Do not overcook.
Remove gently from the water; drain and chill.

title: potato refrigerator dough
directions: Mix 1 cup of lukewarm water with sugar and salt.
Sprinkle yeast over 1/2 cup lukewarm water; stir yeast until dissolved.
Add to first mixture.
Add slightly beaten eggs and shortening.
Mix in first with spoon, then with hand, the potatoes and flour.
Knead until smooth.
Place in refrigerator in large Tupperware bowl. About 2 hours before baking, shape rolls into desired shape. Cover; let rise until light (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter and jelly cookies
directions: Stir together flour, shortening, peanut butter, sugar, egg and salt until smooth.
For each cookie, roll one teaspoonful dough into ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; with finger, make dent in center of ball.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Carefully remove to rack (cookies will be tender).
Cool and fill hollows with jelly.
Makes about 36.

title: spiced maple cider
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients except liqueur, bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 20 minutes. Remove orange slices and spices.
Add liqueur if desired.
Serve warm.

title: frozen caramel pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine. Pack into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Divide popped corn into 2 large baking pans.
Mix brown sugar, butter and corn syrup and salt in saucepan; cook and stir over medium heat until it bubbles around the edge.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Take pan off heat and stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour equal amounts of the mixture over the popcorn.
Stir until popcorn is coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: korn's pie crust(great)
directions: Pour hot water over lard; stir until smooth and add salt and vinegar.
Add flour until dough comes off hands easily.
Yields 4 (2 crust) pies.

title: creme puff cake
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Mix pudding with milk, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half of mixture over crackers, then cover with another layer of crackers. Use remaining pudding mixture and a third layer of crackers.
Let set in refrigerator at least an hour, then cover with a thin drizzle of powdered sugar using remaining ingredients.
It is best if left in refrigerator 24 hours or at least overnight.

title: old-fashioned baked beans
directions: Wash beans thoroughly; place in a 4-quart saucepan.
Add enough water to cover 2 inches above beans.
Let soak overnight. Drain off water.
Cover with fresh cold water.
Add soda; bring to a boil.
Drain again and rinse well.
Cover with cold water. Bring to a boil.
Place onion slices in bean pot or deep casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients, except salt pork.
Add hot beans and enough boiling water to barely cover beans.
Place strips of salt pork over top.
Cover and bake at 250° for 9 to 10 hours or until beans are tender, adding more boiling water as liquid evaporates.
Remove cover.
Bake for one hour longer to let salt pork become crisp and brown.
Serve piping hot, plain or with catsup or chili sauce.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add all of the ingredients, mix and form into a ball.
Put in skillet, add 1/2 cup water and bake with lid at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.
Check often.
If should get dry, add more water.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Add eggs to sugar, one at a time.
Add flour and salt, then baking powder.
Melt butter and sour cream; add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mary's chicken stew
directions: Dredge chicken in seasoned flour.
Fry bacon in large skillet, remove and reserve.
Place chicken in skillet and brown.
Transfer to large casserole Dutch oven.
Add vegetables.
Pour over all the chicken broth.
Sprinkle with the sage and crumbled bacon.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until the chicken and vegetables are tender.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with chipped beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon and arrange in dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 275°, uncovered, for approximately 3 hours. Twenty minutes before baking is finished, sprinkle cheese over chicken and finish cooking.
Serves 8.

title: white trash candy
directions: Combine both Chex cereals, pretzels and peanuts in large bowl. Melt the coating in microwave at 50% power, stirring every 2 minutes.
Pour melted coating over dry mix and stir until all is coated well.
Line two cookie sheets with wax paper and spread mix all over.
Chill at least 15 minutes.
Remove from pans by breaking apart like peanut brittle.
Store in Ziploc bags.
Refrigerate in humid weather.
Makes a very large amount of candy.
May want to halve the recipe.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 35 minutes.
Top with the following topping.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package, leaving liquid in, if desired. Blend soup, butter and seasonings. Combine with broccoli; simmer on top of stove or crock-pot until hot. This can be doubled easily. Serves 4. Can do ahead.

title: eggless jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well with an electric mixer.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes in a tube pan.

title: jessie's pie crust
directions: Mix the flour, salt and sugar into a bowl.
Add and mix in the shortening.
Beat in small bowl the egg, vinegar and water.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture; mix well.
Refrigerate a couple of hours before using.

title: pork chops southern style
directions: Flour chops.
Brown on both sides in hot oil.
Place in baking dish.
Add corn, green pepper and tomato sauce; pour over chops. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: mushroom chicken(serves 4)
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
In large bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken picante
directions: Butterfly chicken breasts or pound to even thickness, about 1/2-inch thick.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder, chili powder and rosemary.
Heat oil to medium-high in frypan and cook each side of chicken, about 1 minute.
Set chicken aside and keep warm.
In same pan, add picante and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer until mixture is reduced in half.
On sheet pan, arrange chicken. Cover each piece with cooked picante mixture and top with cheese. Place under broiler until cheese bubbles and is brown.
Serve with yellow or Spanish rice.

title: easy camp stew
directions: Saute
onion in margarine;
add all of the ingredients. Stir thoroughly.
Cook on medium for 30 minutes.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Use kitchen syringe to inject dressing or Cajun mixture into turkey meat.
Heat oil in deep fryer or fish fryer to 325°.
Fry turkey for 30 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 185°. Fried turkeys can be frozen whole; cool, wrap in foil and freeze.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown green pepper, onion and hamburger in a tablespoon of fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Can be kept in refrigerator several days.
Heat before serving.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Mix the water, yeast, sugar, margarine, 1 egg and 3 cups of flour together.
Then work in the remaining 3 cups as needed until the dough is stiff.
Refrigerate the dough 2 to 24 hours.

title: old-fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Line two 8 inch pie plates with unbaked pastry.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, and remaining ingredients in order given.
Bake in a preheated very hot oven 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat quickly (leave oven door slightly ajar about three minutes) to slow oven 325°, and continue baking for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted in center of filling.
Serve warm or cold.
(We prefer the pie warm, topped with ice cream.)

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Break the cheese into nuggets.
Fold in the mayonnaise. Dissolve the dry ingredients in the vinegar.
Add the oil to the mayonnaise while beating.
Whip in the vinegar and cold water. Mix well.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, beaten egg, flour and pineapple juice.
Cook on medium heat until thickened, approximately 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Combine apples, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Add peanuts and marshmallows.
Stir in cooked custard mixture after it is completely cooled; mix well.
Chill well before serving.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in an 8-ounce measure.
Cook for 4 minutes at 100% power.
Add the peanuts and cook for 3 or 4 more minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla and cook for 1 more minute. Add soda and stir until mixture is light and foamy.
Pour and spread onto a greased flexible baking sheet.
Cool for 1/2 hour and then break into pieces.
Store in an airtight container.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Melt butter in
baking pan at 250°.
Mix other ingredients. Remove melted butter from oven and coat chicken first in the butter, then
the crumb mixture.
Lay chicken in remaining butter in pan,
top with any remaining crumb mixture, sprinkle with paprika if
desired
and
bake,
uncovered, at 350° until tender, about 1
hour.
Baste
chicken
a
time
or two during baking. Cover with
foil
if coating starts to brown too much before chicken is tender.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Cream together oleo and sugars until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine margarine, powdered sugar, flour and salt.
Mix at low speed.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 300°.
Beat eggs; add sugar, flour (1/2 cup) and lemon juice. Blend.
Pour over crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut in squares.

title: sopapillasroswell, new mexico
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.

title: cheap chili
directions: Simmer all together for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: my coconut cake
directions: Mix oil, oleo and sugar until creamy.
Add whole egg, then add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add vanilla and half cup buttermilk and beat.
Add half flour and beat good.
Add rest of milk and flour, beating good.
Pour into 3 greased cake pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: maple heights baked beans
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Combine with all other ingredients, except bacon.
Place in lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 minutes.
Top with bacon and mix in. Bake 5 minutes more.

title: seafood salad
directions: In large salad bowl, place ingredients in order given; toss lightly to mix.
Cover and chill.
Serve on crisp letuce leaves.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix meats, eggs, cheese, parsley and 3 cloves of garlic in a large container. Take crust off of Italian bread. Wet, then squeeze out water and put into mixture and form into balls the size of an egg. Put the meatballs into a baking pan and brown them in the oven. Put them into sauce and cook for 2 hours or fry meatballs in olive oil until brown and then add to tomato sauce.

title: rock cakes
directions: Sift the flour into a medium sized bowl.
Cut in the butter or margarine until it resembles breadcrumbs.
Add the dry ingredients, a little grated nutmeg and the egg, well beaten.
Add the milk, being careful not to make the mixture too moist.
Put in small heaps on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Divide popped corn between 2 greased baking pans, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, or 1 large roaster.
In saucepan, heat sugar, butter, syrup and salt.
Stir occasionally until bubbles from around edges.
Continue to cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in soda until foamy.
Pour over popped corn, stirring until corn is well coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour out on greased foil or waxed paper.

title: easy fruit cobbler(a cup of cobbler)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Put margarine in baking dish and place in oven to melt.
Meanwhile, put sugar, flour and milk in bowl and mix well.
Put fruit on top of melted margarine.
Add flour mixture on top and bake 30 minutes or until brown.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and blend in ginger, cinnamon and salt. Add egg and beat. Blend in molasses and milk. Stir together baking soda and flour. Combine all ingredients.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 325° in an 8 x 10-inch greased baking pan.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Add red chili beans.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch dish; cover with remaining ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° to melt the cheese.

title: cheerios oat cookies
directions: *If children under 4 years old, omit raisins.

title: microwave nine bean soup(spicy)
directions: Microwave Power:
High (10).
Microwave Time: 2 Hours and
10 to 20 minutes.

title: mud pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Mix cookies, butter and nuts.
Press mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool. Pour slightly melted ice cream in pan.
Sprinkle a few crushed Oreo cookies on top and freeze.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add the cranberry sauce.
Stir well.
Add crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Add celery and nuts. Refrigerate for 8 hours.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: katie's breakfast potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in oven until done.
Cool.
Slice potatoes lengthwise and scoop out.
Scramble eggs.
Cook eggs in butter, leaving eggs still soft.
Mix eggs with potato meat, sour cream and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Heap mix into potato shells.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel brownies
directions: First melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Combine cake mix, butter, pecans and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix all together, then put half of the batter in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Pour caramel over 1/2 batter, sprinkle all chocolate chips and spoon rest of batter on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: honey dijon dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Will keep for approximately 2 weeks.
Discard when it begins to separate.

title: bread and butter pickle
directions: Pour over pickles what you
need
and save remainder for another time.
Enough for 4 to 5 quarts.
Put
to
cold pack and when begins to boil, remove at once.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie plate and chill.

title: beer muffins
directions: Mix until moistened, but no more.
Do not beat.
Pour into 8 or 12 greased muffin tins or cups.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: choc-oat-chip cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well. Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, pineapple, nuts and Cool Whip, then add dry jello from box.
Mix together and let set.

title: fanny may fudge
directions: Heat butter, sugar and milk until warm, not hot.
Add marshmallows.
Heat until marshmallows melt.
Bring to boil and remove from heat.
Add Hershey bar, chocolate chips and nuts. Stir (do not beat) until all is dissolved.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate to set.
Cut in squares.

title: glorious tossed salad
directions: Chop and mix all vegetables.
Add in cheese and dressing. Toss.
Top with bacon bits and croutons.
Preparation time: 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: austin's awesome avocado dip
directions: Peel, remove seed and lightly puree avocados.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly with fork.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add cornstarch; mix until smooth. Stir sugar and vinegar, making a smooth sauce.
Add beets; let cook slowly until thoroughly heated.

title: puddin's never fail pie crust
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening well.
Combine all liquid ingredients including the egg and mix well.
Add dry ingredients until well moistened.
Chill thoroughly.
Add a little more flour to roll out.

title: blackberry jelly
directions: Sort and wash ripe berries; remove stems or caps.
Crush berries and extract juice.
Measure juice in kettle; stir in sugar.
Place on high heat and stirring constantly, bring quickly to rolling boil that cannot be stirred down.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and bake in 2 (15-inch) greased and floured pizza pans.
Spread mixture in pans and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Check center for doneness.
Cool. Spread with Cool Whip.

title: butter pecan pound cake
directions: Allow butter to soften.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour and blend well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until a pick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine egg, salt and sugar.
Add milk gradually, then add coconut and mix.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Decrease heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes or so longer.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook in water and bouillon cubes. When done, drain the water.
Add sour cream and cheese to carrots. Cook onions in margarine.
Mix all together and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: corn flake clusters
directions: In a sauce pan, put butterscotch and chocolate chips in. Stir over low heat until melted, remove from heat and stir in peanuts and Corn Flakes. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and let set up.

title: green noodles with mushroom and olive sauce
directions: Saute garlic in oil over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Pour in wine and cook until mushrooms are cooked.
Add olives and pine nuts and saute 8 minutes.
Add chopped parsley.
Cook and drain noodles.
Toss with sauce and serve.

title: new england crab cakes
directions: Spray unheated large skillet with nonstick spray.
Add the celery, onion and parsley.
Cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
Remove from heat.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Place chops in large baking dish and place sliced onions on top of chops.
Mix soup with milk and pour over chops.
Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven an hour or until tender.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar; beat.
Add eggs; beat.
Add flour and other ingredients; beat.
Add nuts last.
Pour in 2 loaf pans.
Top with nut halves.
Bake at 350°.
Test when done with toothpick.
This freezes well.

title: pat-a-pie crust(for those who think they cannot make pie crusts)
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Whip oil and milk, pour into flour mixture.
Mix with fork until flour is completely dampened. Shape in pan with fingers.
Press evenly over bottom and sides of pan.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Fill with favorite pie filling.
Reserve 1/3 of dough to crumble on top if making fruit pie.

title: company mashed potatoes
directions: Bring 4 cups water to boil.
Add salt, potato flakes, sour cream and cream cheese to water.
Mix with mixer until well blended.
Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put potatoes into dish and top with dots of oleo.
Sprinkle parsley flakes over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until slightly browned.

title: creamy rice and vegetables
directions: Bring vegetables, milk, garlic salt and basil to boil in large saucepan.
Stir in rice and cheese; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes or until milk is absorbed.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring warm water, sugar and coffee to rolling boil.
Let simmer for 1 hour and add vanilla and vodka.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: arlene's apple crumble cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 ounce flour.
Squeeze lemon juice over apples.
Toss apples with sugar mixture.
Put in baking dish.
Mix butter, rest of flour and cinnamon.
Add rind and rest of sugar; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until top is golden brown.

title: easy cheesy turkey loaf
directions: Combine ingredients except catsup.
Mix lightly and place in a nonstick loaf pan.
Spread top with catsup.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings; 221 calories per serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix 1st three ingredients; roll into 3/4 inch balls and coat with crushed cereal.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut up.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
In bottom of greased pan place broccoli. Layer chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, and pour evenly over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Cover with crumbs and pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix the peaches, tapioca, cornstarch, nutmeg, white and brown sugars, lemon juice and margarine.
Pour in crust.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions, adding snap peas after 18 minutes of cooking.
While rice is cooking, pound chicken to 1/2-inch thickness.
Place on rack of broiler pan.
Combine honey, soy sauce, ginger, garlic and red pepper.
Spoon half of mixture over chicken; let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Broil 4-inches from heat for 6 minutes; turn and baste with remaining honey mixture.
Continue broiling until chicken is cooked through, about 4 minutes.
Serve chicken along side rice; sprinkle rice with black pepper to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in hot waffle iron for 1 or 2 minutes, until crisp.
Remove and cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Enjoy!

title: sweet-sour cucumbers
directions: In large bowl combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 45 minutes to blend flavors, stirring mixture occasionally.
Makes 12 servings.

title: veal marsala
directions: Pound meat and dredge in flour. Brown in oil. After meat has all browned, place onion, mushrooms, garlic and parsley in skillet and cook until onion is transparent, about 10 minutes.
Place in pot over meat. Add tomato sauce and wine. Cook over low heat for about 2 hours. About 30 minutes before serving, add peas and continue cooking.

title: italian cream cake with frosting
directions: Combine soda and buttermilk and let stand for a few minutes. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream the sugar, oleo and shortening. Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat after each.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and fold in egg whites.
Add pecans and coconut.
Put in 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Slice apples and leave peelings on.
Soak in lemon water to keep apples from turning brown.
Drain.
Combine cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla.
Mix and place in small bowl.
Arrange apples nicely around bowl mixing the colors of apples to make attractive.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar, flour and melted butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven.
Reduce heat to 325° after 10 minutes.
Bake about 30 minutes at 325°.

title: red beans and brown rice(texas-style)
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onions and garlic in oil until tender. Add the beans, chilies, broth, ketchup, molasses, chili powder, vinegar and soy sauce. Let come to a boil; reduce heat to a simmer. Let cook for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve over brown rice. Makes about 4 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling and pineapple in a large pan; top with the cake mix.
Mix the butter, coconut and pecans.
Pour over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, corn syrup and peanuts in pan and boil until peanuts begin to pop and mixture turns light brown.
Then add soda.
Pour out on greased surface and allow to cool.
Break in pieces.

title: golden wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients into a large pan.
Heat to boiling point, reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and strain.
Pour hot wassail into mugs.
Can garnish with floaters of thin orange slices studded with cloves.
Makes 9 cups.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and pour into buttered dish.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; add all ingredients except 1/2 cup Ro-Tel and tortillas.
Cook 10 minutes.
Layer tortillas, meat and cheese.
Pour remaining 1/2 cup Ro-Tel on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes its own crust.

title: hershey's chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture.
Add chocolate syrup.
Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: lasagne(very good)
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, ground pork, onion and garlic in large saucepan or Dutch oven until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain all fat.
Add tomatoes and break up with fork.
Stir in tomato sauce, 2 tablespoons parsley flakes, 2 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and the basil.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 1 hour or until mixture is the consistency of spaghetti sauce.

title: strawberry impossible pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender or mixer.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's shipwreck stew
directions: Coat casserole dish with canola oil or spray with Pam. Arrange ingredients in order in casserole.
Mix salt, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce and water together and pour over.
Cover with foil or lid.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Check middle for doneness.

title: bible cake
directions: In large heart with love mixer, soften and cream Genesis 18; slowly beat in Isaiah 7.
In small corner of heart, beat Job 39 well and add to this mixture.
Sift together 1 Samuel 28, 1 Kings 19, Matthew 21, Exodus 30 and Luke 14.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Through your thoughts, fold 2 Samuel 16 and Genesis 43. Grease a 9-inch tube pan with Judges 5.
Line with waxed paper. Pour in batter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Lower temperature to 325°.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and enjoy.

title: bean dip
directions: Combine all in a crock-pot and serve hot with nacho chips. Also great as a hot dog sauce and over a baked potato.

title: chunky guacamole
directions: In a medium bowl, combine tomato, jalapeno, green onion, garlic, lemon juice and salt; mix well.
Peel and seed avocado; cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Stir avocado cubes into tomato mixture. Serve immediately.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Pour equal amounts of milk and water in top of double boiler. Heat to "almost" scald.
Add broccoli and cheese.
When cheese is melted and broccoli thawed and cooked some, put this through food mill so mixture is creamy and broccoli no longer has to be chewed. You want a very smooth soup.

title: surprise pudding
directions: Put all ingredients in a shaker and shake for a couple of minutes.
Pour immediately into a small bowl and let set for 2 to 5 minutes and eat with a spoon.

title: blueberry goop
directions: Put on top of jello mixture after it sets.

title: orange float
directions: Reconstitute orange juice as directed; divide among 8 large glasses.
Add ice cream and fill each with club soda or ginger ale.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Place chicken on top. Sprinkle onion soup mix over top.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 320° for 1 hour and don't peek.

title: hobo dinners
directions: Place one patty of hamburger on piece of aluminum foil.
Make the aluminum pieces large enough to hold several ingredients stacked on top of the patties.
Layer potatoes, onion, bell pepper, salt, pepper and a pat of butter on top of each hamburger patty.
Close and seal the aluminum packs.
Place on grill and cook for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Clean shortening, sugar and pumpkin.
Add egg and mix well. Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Stir in raisins and chocolate chips.
Drop from spoon to ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost warm.

title: baw baw's chili sauce
directions: Put into large pot and cook on real low heat until it is real thick.
Put in jars and seal.

title: brisket
directions: In a medium skillet, saute onions until lightly browned.
Add bell pepper and mushrooms; saute until soft and set aside.
Place 1/3 of sauteed mixture on a large sheet of heavy foil in a shallow roasting pan.
Place meat on top and add remaining sauteed mixture.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and pepper.
Pour wine around meat.
Arrange carrots and potatoes around meat.
Wrap airtight in foil, allowing space for gravy to form.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 3 to 4 hours.
Slice meat across grain and serve with pan juices and vegetables.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Place in ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Punch 2 holes in flour mixture. Pour oil in one hole; pour vinegar in remaining hole. Pour cold water on top. Add vanilla and stir. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: gene's simple (barbecue) sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
(Add red pepper flakes for hot version.) Use to baste meat in final minutes of grilling time.
Also great just drizzled over Ripple potato chips.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Pour chilled evaporated milk into a medium-size bowl and whip with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Mix water, lemon juice and jello in microwave bowl and heat for 1 minute.
Stir to dissolve gelatin.
Mix whipped milk and gelatin mixture with mixer until thoroughly blended.
Pour into baked pie crust and chill until fully set.
Garnish with kiwi fruit.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut thin slice from top.
Scoop out insides. Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/4 cup cheese and paprika to the potatoes.
Mash.
Spoon into shells.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: butter sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg, then sifted dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill dough.
Place on cookie sheet in small balls and flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until golden, about 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
In large mixer bowl, combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with water to butter mixture.
Blend just until combined.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans to wire racks.
Cool completely.
Frost with chocolate buttercream frosting.

title: chicken-asparagus casserole
directions: Mix soup and cheese; heat until cheese is melted. Do not boil. Add chicken and pimentos and mix well.
In casserole dish, arrange a layer of cheese sauce, a layer of asparagus, a layer of cracker crumbs and repeat layers.
Dot top with butter and bake in a 350° oven until browned, approximately 10 minutes.

title: aw maw's potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in Dutch oven and cover with water. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until tender; drain. Cover and chill. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients like pie crust.
Take 1 cup of mixture and set aside.
To rest of mixture, add the egg, milk, soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat well and pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle cup of mixture over cake, then add 12 crushed Heath bars over mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chutney cheese roll
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature 6 to 8 hours.
Roll 1/2 of soft cheese between 2 pieces of wax paper to 1/8-inch thickness.
Repeat with other half.
Spread softened cream cheese over the rolled out cheese to cover it completely.
Toast nuts 10 minutes in 300° oven.
In food processor or blender, chop nuts; add remaining ingredients and spread over the cheese.
Roll the cheese with the help of the wax paper, sealing the ends of the roll.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crackers.
May be frozen.

title: cold pickled vegetables
directions: Drain beans, peas and pimentos into colander.
Rinse with cold water and drain thoroughly.
Combine sugar, vinegar, water, oil and salt in a bowl.
Add celery, onion and drained vegetables.
Mix well.
Cover and chill overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days at least.
To serve, drain well.
Serves 12.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Drain the fruit cocktail.
Add bananas, marshmallows and coconut. Fold in whipped cream. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and chill.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix ingredients and 1/2 can noodles in baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 can noodles.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and put in pan.
Cover with crushed potato chips or sliced almonds.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: daddy burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into 6 to 8 burgers. Cook on outside grill or under the broiler.
Serve on a bun; add cheese for cheeseburgers.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add egg, milk and shortening (oil).
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Crumble cornbread and add white bread, onion, celery, eggs, salt, pepper, sage, poultry seasoning and stock (may use canned stock and some water).
Mix well; the mixture should be the consistency of thick cornbread batter.
Pour into a large, oblong pan, greased or sprayed with Pam.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until firm and browned on top.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until tender and skins are very crisp, about 1 1/4 hours.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out centers into bowl.
Add butter and mash until smooth.
Fold in cheese, sour cream, chives, salt, pepper and bacon.
Mound mixture in potato shells and bake another 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: diabetic chicken spaghetti
directions: Combine chicken and water to cover in large skillet.
Cover and boil.
Reduce heat, simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain well. Chop chicken; set aside.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain and set aside.
Combine soup, milk and seasoning in saucepan.
Stir to blend.
Layer spaghetti, chicken, soup mixture and mushrooms in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325°
for 30 to 45 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: grandma's garlic grits
directions: Cook grits in salt water per package directions.
Put 3/4 of margarine and cheese in grits.
Let cool slightly.
Add eggs and milk.
Pour into buttered casserole and add rest of cheese. Sprinkle cornflakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beet salad
directions: Grate beets real fine into a salad bowl.
Add cabbage and carrots.
Beat together the lemon juice, honey, oil and salt and pour over beet mixture.
Toss and chill.
Sprinkle seeds over top. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to boil (hard).
Boil one minute. Set aside to cool.
It takes a lot of beating.
Creamy and excellent!

title: potato vegetable chowder
directions: In saucepan, over low heat, melt margarine.
Stir in onion. Saute until tender.
Stir in flour, bouillon, thyme and pepper. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly. Gradually stir in milk and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Stir in potatoes, ham and vegetables. Reduce heat. Simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 (1 1/2 cup) servings. Freezes well.

title: chili bean bake
directions: Cook oil, meat and onion until lightly brown.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese.
Stir gently to mix. Pour into greased casserole and sprinkle with cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 325°. Serve over buttered noodles with tossed salad.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressings and cheese; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill before serving.

title: cheeseburger meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pecan praline
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and milk to soft ball stage; cool 10 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat 2 minutes.
Add nuts and stir until loses gloss.
Drop by tablespoon on buttered dish.

title: chocolate delight bars
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients.
Sift the next 3 ingredients and stir in.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips.
Return to oven 1 minute. Spread on top.
Beat eggs and sugar; stir in butter, vanilla and nut meats.
Place over melted chocolate chips and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Bake at 350°F for 1 hour.

title: easy overnight coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon in large mixing bowl.
Add buttermilk, oleo and eggs.
Beat on low speed of mixer until moistened, then beat on medium speed 3 minutes.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup brown sugar, the nuts and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or 8 to 12 hours.
Uncover and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
To reheat, cover with foil and put in 350° oven for 5 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel and slice apples (enough to fill your baking dish). Spray dish with Pam. Layer apples. Cut up stick of butter into patties and lay on top of apples. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples and butter. Bake at 300° for about an hour.

title: hash casserole
directions: Mix cornmeal, salt and cold water.
Add to boiling water. Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan and push up on sides of pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Fill with corned beef hash.
Pour ketchup over top and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with pineapple.
Stir in Cool Whip. Add apples and nuts; mix.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in pieces using the tops and some of the smaller stems.
Mix all ingredients together and let set 2 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: orange-candied sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cook in water to cover in saucepan for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender; drain.
Cool.
Peel potatoes; cut lengthwise into 1/2-inch slices.
Melt margarine in large skillet. Stir in marmalade, orange juice, lemon juice and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes, turning potatoes occasionally.
Spoon onto serving dish; sprinkle with coconut.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: top me twice cake
directions: Grease 12 x 8-inch cake pan.
Combine sugar, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
At low speed, add flour, soda and pineapple; mix 1 minute.
Pour into pan. Sprinkle with mix of brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Just before cake is done, prepare sauce.
Pour over warm cake.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Spread sauce over the bottom of a 9-inch pie plate or another shallow serving dish.
Carefully spread sour cream over sauce. Sprinkle cheese and remaining ingredients over all.
Cover and chill.
Serve with crisp corn chips.

title: plumcake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat the butter until creamy, then add the eggs and continue beating.
Add the sugar and beat until fluffy.
Stir the flour and the baking powder into the dough. Spread the dough into an 8-inch spring-form pan (buttered) and bake it around 45 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Remove the sides and bottom of pan and cool on a rack.
Is good warm or cold.

title: rice krispie rolls
directions: Crush Rice Krispies and set aside.
Melt margarine, set aside. Mix flour,
shortening,
milk
and pour out on floured dough board.
Roll
out
in
thickness of about 1/2 inch.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch
biscuit
cutter,
then
take knife and cut in half. Put Rice
Krispies in plastic bag, dip biscuit halves in margarine, drop in bag
and
shake
it
well.
Put
these on a cookie sheet and
bake
at
(preheat oven) for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Combine jello and crushed pineapple with juice. Heat until jello dissolves. Remove from heat. Blend in buttermilk, coconut and pecans. Fold in Cool Whip. Place in 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Chill until firm.

title: better than sex cake #3
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, oil and water.
Beat until blended. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into large greased tube pan (angel food size).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: yam roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes with electric mixer.
(This is an important step.)
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 1 x 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan that has been well-greased and floured. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until done.
When done, turn out on a tea towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Cool. When cool, unroll and fill.

title: one-step lasagne
directions: Combine water with spaghetti sauce in bowl.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with 1 1/2 cups of sauce.
Arrange a layer of uncooked noodles, slightly overlapping, on top of sauce. Spread half the Ricotta and half the Mozzarella over noodles. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Add another layer of sauce. Repeat with another layer of noodles, the remaining Ricotta and Mozzarella and 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Top with layer of noodles. Pour remaining sauce over, spreading evenly to cover edges of noodles.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan.

title: cinnamon toast cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Add salt, flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Blend in nuts.
Divide and shape dough into 6 loaves.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Place 3 loaves on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; slice loaves.
Dip sliced cookies in cinnamon sugar and return to oven.
Toast for 10 minutes.
Repeat with the remaining 3 loaves. Cool and serve.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: pear relish
directions: Peel and core pears. Grind pears, onions and peppers in food chopper.
Place in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 30 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Remove spice bag. Pour into hot sterilized jars. Leave 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: reindeer cookies
directions: Place the cookie dough in the freezer for 15 minutes or until firm. Preheat the oven to 350°. Cut the dough into 24 slices and place the slices 2-inches apart on a large ungreased cookie sheet. Pinch each slice 1/3 of the way down, until 1/2-inch wide. Position 2 pretzels at the top of each slice to form antlers, then use brown M&M's to create eyes and red ones to make noses. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper chops.
Put in shallow pan.
Combine brown sugar, ketchup and water.
Spoon over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover for first half of baking time.
Uncover for last half.
Turn chops at least once.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Combine the butter, milk,
brown
and white sugars in a pan. Let it come to a boil 1 or 2 minutes.
Take off the heat and add the cornflakes,
pecans
and peanut butter; beat until smooth. Drop onto waxed
paper
by the teaspoonful.
Allow to stand for at least 20 minutes before serving.

title: nut bread delight
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350° in loaf pan.

title: pudding pizza
directions: Allow cookie dough to warm slightly.
Place dough on an ungreased pizza pan or baking dish.
Press evenly to bottom and sides to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool.

title: tabouli salad
