directions: Soak bulgar in the lemon juice. Set aside. Prepare chopped ingredients. Add to bulgar when lemon juice has been absorbed. Mix all together, add salt and pepper and add olive oil last. Adjust seasoning.
This is a nice vegetarian salad served with pita bread.

title: tomato - pear relish
directions: Cook 1 hour slow.
Add pimentos the last 3 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given and mix lightly.
Pack firmly into a greased small loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Pour off juice and turn loaf onto warm platter.
Serve with mixture of mushroom soup and 1/4 cup milk, stirred constantly. Pour some of the sauce over the loaf to serve and the rest in a side dish.

title: liver in herbed tomato sauce
directions: Cut liver into strips 1 inch wide.
Cover with boiling water. Then drain thoroughly.
Mix flour, seasoned salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add liver, a few pieces at a time, and shake until coated.
Set aside.

title: dreamy apricot salad
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and water in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar and gelatin.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit; set aside to cool.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Put potatoes in a greased bake dish.
Pour first mixture over potatoes.
Mix cornflakes and the last margarine together; sprinkle on top of mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add nuts and spices, then flour and fruit last.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° (15 for electric stove).
For softer cookie, bake 8 to 9 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 3 items in bowl.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with second pie crust.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and oil.
Pour hot water and mix.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Blend in egg.
Make 8 to 10 patties.
Cook in hot oil in skillet or in the oven on greased cooking sheet until browned on both sides.
Takes 10 to 15 minutes on top of stove and 20 to 25 minutes in the oven.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder and salt; sift again.
Cream butter or margarine thoroughly; gradually add sugar, creaming until fluffy.
Add beaten eggs, flavoring and liquid.
Add and blend in flour, one-third at a time. Dough should be soft but just firm enough to roll out on a lightly floured board to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with floured 2 to 3-inch cookie cutter.
Lift with spatula to ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at shelf position B (below center of oven) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Cookies may be brushed with milk or buttermilk and sprinkled with sugar before baking.
Can also make these as drop cookies; edges will be brown on these.

title: zucchini apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° in 8-inch square nonstick baking dish for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: broiled herbed chicken(serves four)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lift the skin of the chicken carefully with your fingers, being careful not to tear it or detach it except from the main part of the flesh. You are forming pockets in it. Soften butter. Chop parsley and blend it in until you have a slightly greenish paste. Add thyme.

title: for goodness sakes salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve the gelatins in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Stir in the milk, pineapple, nuts and horseradish sauce; mix well.
Chill until partially set.
Pour into an oiled 8-cup mold.
Chill for 6 hours or overnight.
Unmold and serve on a bed of lettuce leaves.

title: mother's chicken loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: ham b.b.q.'s
directions: Melt butter, worcestershire sauce and brown sugar in pot. Add ketchup, water and relish to suit.
Add chipped ham that has been pulled apart.
Heat thoroughly.

title: grilled tuna steaks
directions: Cover steaks with dressing and let stand in refrigerator 2 hours.
Twenty minutes before you are ready to cook, preheat grill.
Cook over medium coals for 5 to 10 minutes on each side, until meat flakes easily with a fork.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Stir in corn, cheese and corn bread mix.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Good for church suppers.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Separate rolls into triangles.
Place points inward.
In ungreased pizza pan, press together to form a crust.
Sprinkle with sausage, potatoes and cheese.
Beat eggs, water and seasonings together.
Pour over top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Serves 6 to 8.

title: christmas trees
directions: Cream butter in large mixing bowl; gradually add sugar and gelatin, beating at medium speed.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well. Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Use a cookie gun to shape dough as desired, following the manufacturer's instructions.
Place cookies on ungreased cookie sheet.
Garnish, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: baked noodle ring
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain well and keep hot.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in milk and cream a little at a time.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Add yolks all at once to that mixture.
Continue to cool 1 minute.
Beat egg whites until they hold
peak.

title: banana puddin
directions: After mixing vanilla pudding as directed by the box (wire whisk works great), add Eagle Brand milk; whisk. Then add the Cool Whip; whisk. Lay vanilla wafers on the bottom of the pan you plan to use; top each wafer with a slice of banana. Next pour pudding mixture over bananas. Slide wafers down along the sides of the pan.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in refrigerator until chilled.
Roll out.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: chicken skroodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken; let cool.
Remove meat and cut in bite sized pieces.
Use chicken broth to cook Skroodles.
Follow directions on package for cooking these.
Saute celery and green pepper in butter; add pimentos.
Mix all together.
Add Greek seasoning and salt to taste.
Mixture will be soupy; bake in a 350° oven about 45 minutes or until brown and fairly firm.

title: hollywood casserole
directions: Fry bacon and beef.
Cook noodles; drain and cool.
Dice cheese and add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This casserole may be frozen and cooked later or refrigerated overnight.

title: vinaigrette for salad and tomatoes
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a bowl.
This recipe has been used at LeBistro for 20 years.
Spoon over any fresh salad mixture. Also excellent over tomatoes and asparagus with fresh red onion.

title: spicy fettucine
directions: Brown sausage; add onion, pepper and mushrooms and saute until tender.
Add tomatoes and green chilies.
Simmer 10 minutes or until meat is completely cooked.
Serve over fettucine.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chinese butterscotch clusters
directions: Melt chips over medium heat; remove from heat.
Stir in peanuts and noodles.
Use heaping teaspoonfuls of prepared mixture.
Drop on waxed paper to form clusters.
Let cool before serving.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together.
Great with country style ribs.

title: cranberry relish(sugar-free)
directions: Place all ingredients in food grinder (leave orange unpeeled). Mix thoroughly. Refrigerate 1 or 2 days. Add another orange if too tart.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Mix the sugar and flour in a bowl; do not sift.
Combine margarine, cocoa, Crisco and water in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil; pour over dry ingredients and stir.
Add eggs and buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Bake in an 11 x 18-inch pan for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Sprinkle 1 1/4 teaspoons salt over top of cabbage.
While cabbage wilts, mix in jar or shaker: sugar, mayonnaise, vinegar and milk.
Stir cabbage and add dressing.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix desired amount to taste into boiling water.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cut potatoes into bite-size pieces.
Melt margarine, soup, cheese and onion together.
Then stir in potatoes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli until tender; add onion.
Mix rice and broccoli with Cheez Whiz. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel chews
directions: Bring to 240°.
Pour into a buttered sheet cake pan.
Cool, cut and wrap.

title: chocoholic's petite custards
directions: Place eggs, chocolate chips, sugar, vanilla and salt in blender.
Heat milk just to simmer and add to ingredients in blender. Whirl on low for 1 full minute.
Pour into demitasse cups.
Chill until firm for 3 hours or more.
Serve with a dollop of whipped cream. Can be frozen. Can add walnuts.
Can be made with Bailey's Irish cream in lieu of milk.

title: dump cake
directions: Stir cherries (do not drain), water and sugar together in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Cut up butter on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: continental chicken
directions: Line bottom of pan with the dried beef.
Wrap each breast with bacon slice and put on top of dried beef.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Pour off bacon fat.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Reduce heat to 350° and cover. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter in large bowl.
Gradually add sugar, mixing well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: oriental wild rice casserole
directions: Precook wild rice in 3 cups water until tender.
Don't drain. (Cover with water and bring to a boil; turn heat down and simmer 45 to 60 minutes.)
Brown ground beef and saute onion, celery and green pepper.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and sour cream. Beat until blended.
Stir in melted butter.
If thinner pancakes are desired, add more buttermilk.

title: salty chicken
directions: Skin chicken; place on grill.
Baste with sauce made from ingredients for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: mummies
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Separate crescent roll squares from roll.
Spread each square and roll up a hotdog in crescent roll. Bake on a cookie sheet for 12-15 minutes (until rolls are golden brown).
Remove from oven and let cool.
Once cooled, dip toothpick in mustard and dot two eyes on one end of each hot dog.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well and fry in deep fat. Wonderful to serve with fried fish.

title: 9 day slaw
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Take Wesson oil, vinegar and sugar; bring to a boil. Pour over cabbage mixture while hot.
Cover and put in icebox.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and blend into butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: frito pie
directions: Heat chili. Spread a layer of Fritos, chili and then cheese. Repeat this order. Heat at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: clam fritters
directions: Drain clams, reserving 1/3 cup juice.
Combine Bisquick, salt and thyme.
Add egg, clam juice and clams.
Stir.
Drop from tablespoons into hot oil.
Fry until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 24 and may be frozen.
For a couple recipe, use 3 cans of clams.

title: vegetarian spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil. Add tomatoes and break up with spoon. Add tomato paste, vegetables (raw ones first); anything goes, peppers, carrots, zucchini, mushrooms, corn, squash, broccoli, beans, etc.
Add spices.
Simmer about 45 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Stir in 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese if you like the sauce to be thicker.
Very low in calories and fat.

title: ranch mashed potatoes
directions: Omit salt from mashed potatoes.

title: potato-corn chowder
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Steam carrots, broccoli and pea pods together until crisp-tender; cool.
Cook fettuccine in chicken broth, just until tender; drain and cool.
Combine vegetables and pasta.
Add basil to prepared salad dressing.
Toss gently into pasta.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and fresh parsley.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt shortening in heavy Dutch oven over high fire.
Add flour and stir until it is light brown.
Lower heat; add shrimp and cook 3 minutes or until pink.
Add garlic, onion, parsley and bell pepper and cook 2 minutes longer.
Raise heat; gradually add water, then remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Serve very hot over fluffy rice.
Serves 4. Doubles easily.
Freezes well.

title: norwegian slaw
directions: Mix together chopped or shredded cabbage with salt.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Boil the sugar and vinegar and add to the cabbage. Then add the mustard seed, celery seed, green pepper and celery; mix well.
Keeps several days in Tupperware or plastic containers. Use as desired.

title: ethel's gooseberry cobbler
directions: Line 9-inch square pan with pie crust.
Mix together flour and sugar.
Spread half of the mixture over the pie crust in the pan. Dot with butter.
Add gooseberries and water.
Sprinkle remaining flour and sugar mixture over the berries; dot with butter again. Cover with top crust.
Sprinkle a little sugar on top and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: diabetes peach pie
directions: Mix tapioca into white grape juice and let soak 10 minutes. Add lemon juice and cook until thickened.
Pour over peaches and turn into pastry-lined pie tin.
Top with pastry topping.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then lower to 375°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer. Yields 8 servings.

title: dove buttered biscuits
directions: Mix altogether.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake until brown at 400°.

title: moravian white christmas cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients to butter.
Add it to liquid.
Chill several hours and roll out.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: quick tomato jam
directions: Boil tomatoes with sugar for 10 minutes.
Add sliced lemon and lemon gelatin; boil fo 10 minutes.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: mudder's buttermilk pies
directions: Mix sugar and flour together in a bowl. Add eggs, buttermilk, butter and vanilla to bowl. Pour mixture into 2 pie crusts and bake in oven at 350°. Makes 2 pies.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix lettuce, cheese, onion and beans.
This can be covered and stirred in refrigerator.
Just before serving, add chips and dressing.
Toss.

title: hot cranberry salad
directions: Mix and put first three ingredients in buttered casserole. Mix other ingredients together and put on top of casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: kugel cake
directions: Grease 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Cook medium egg noodles.
When done, drain.
Put noodles back in pot.
While still hot, add margarine.
Stir, with a spoon, sugar, vanilla and Ricotta cheese plus sour cream.
Add eggs.
Blend together.

title: glazed yams
directions: Combine the syrup, sugar, water, butter and cinnamon and heat to boiling point.
Pour over yams which have been peeled, halved or sliced and arrange in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix meat, cracker crumbs, milk, salt, pepper, onion and flour. Lightly brown onion in butter; add to meat mixture.
Shape into balls; lightly brown in same pan as onion.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with soup (plus 1/2 can of water).
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then uncover for 10 more minutes.

title: mmmpossible cheesecake
directions: Place milk, vanilla, eggs, sugar, and Bisquick in blender for 15 seconds on high.
Add cream cheese and beat for 2 minutes on high.
Pour into greased pie plate and bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes, until center is firm.
Let cool.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Slice unpeeled potatoes by hand or in food processor and place into a casserole dish sprayed with Pam, sprinkling seasoned salt as you go. Place pats of butter on top of potatoes and sprinkle with chives. Cover with Parmesan cheese, if desired. Cover dish with paper towel or vented plastic wrap. Cook on High in microwave 10 to 12 minutes. Stir midway through cooking cycle. (Cooking time will vary.) Garnish with sour cream or serve as is.

title: beans vinaigrette
directions: Mix all ingredients except green beans and bring to a boil. Drain 4 cans of beans, leaving liquid in 1 can.
Heat all green beans.
Pour dressing mixture over beans and let marinate overnight.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 125.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in salted water 5 minutes, drain. Combine soup and sour cream.
Shred raw carrots and stir in.
Fold in zucchini and onion.
Combine stuffing and margarine.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing in 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon mixture on top then rest of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Select a plump chicken.
Dress.
Cut in pieces.
Place in saucepan.
Cover with boiling water.
Add celery, salt and pepper. Cover.
Simmer slowly until chicken is tender.
Prepare dumpling dough.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown Italian sausage; drain.
In a large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Boil manicotti shells for 8 minutes; drain.
Spray 9 x 13-inch glass dish with Pam.
Cover bottom with Prego (1/2 jar).
Stuff shells with mixture and place in dish.
Cover the stuffed shells with the remaining Prego.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put remaining mixture over the top and bake for another 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes; serve.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy but not stiff. Add pecans and mix until all the nuts are coated.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon. Add to the nuts.
Mix again.
Place on jelly roll pan or shallow tray. Bake in oven at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: In large skillet, cook meat in oil over medium heat until browned and liquid is absorbed.
Add 3 cups water and bouillon. Stir together cornstarch, soy sauce and remaining water.
Add to skillet and cook, stirring constantly until thickened and clear. Add celery, cook over medium 5 to 8 minutes.
Add green peppers; cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve over hot rice or noodles with additional soy sauce if desired.

title: st. patrick's day dinner
directions: Combine beef, garlic, bay leaf and broth.
Cover and cook in a 300° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and add vegetables. Cover again and continue cooking, approximately 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: In saucepan, put oleo, shortening, cocoa and cold water. Bring to boil. Pour hot mixture over flour and sugar. Mix well. Add buttermilk, vanilla, cinnamon, salt, soda and eggs. Mix well. Pour on a greased cookie sheet. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: canned pickled tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half (small tomatoes, leave whole).
Cover tomatoes with vinegar and water mixture.
Slice onions and peppers. Add sugar.
Cook until the tomato skins turn loose from tomatoes. Pour up into jars and seal.
Good with beans, collards and vegetables.

title: skillet chicken and rice
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter; add rice and mushrooms with liquid.
Add dry onion soup and mix.
Add chicken and water; mix well.
Turn skillet to low and cook, covered, about 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: decadent pineapple lime gelatin salad(sugar-free, low sodium)
directions: Bring pineapple with juice to boil in saucepan.
Dissolve gelatin in pineapple well.
Remove from heat.
Add buttermilk and stir until well mixed.
Add pecans and stir.
Spray 8-inch square glass pan with Canola non-stick spray and pour gelatin mixture into pan.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Melt oleo and add sugar and other ingredients.
Bake at 275° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add steamed broccoli and all other ingredients. Mix well. Heat until boiling. Serve in a chafing dish with melba toast.

title: not edible glue dough
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch and glue.
Add water as needed.
Knead dough until workable.

title: crunchy vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl. Mix together sour cream, salad dressing, vinegar, sugar, salt, dill, celery seed and garlic cloves.
Pour over vegetables and toss well.
Pour peas over top. Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: moist n' creamy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes; then poke holes down through cake with a fork.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk. Pour at once into unbaked pie shell. Dash the top with nutmeg. Bake at 475° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° and bake for 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted is clean.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Simple and pretty for your party table.
Serves 15.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Mix well and put into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter, milk and salt in saucepan.
Bring mixture to hard boil.
Let boil 2 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: same day sauerbraten
directions: Brown meat in heavy pot; drain off fat and add 3/4 cup water. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Remove meat and cut in 1/2-inch slices and return to pot.
In another pan, boil 3/4 cup water and remaining ingredients.
Use seasonings to taste.
Pour over meat; cover and simmer until fork-tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Add water if necessary.
Thicken with flour and water mixture off heat. Simmer until flour is cooked, stirring often.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a large pan, add bouillon cubes to water; bring to boil and add chicken breasts. When chicken is done, remove from broth. Return broth to boil and then add 16-ounces thin spaghetti and diced green onions. While spaghetti is cooking, cube chicken breasts.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until done, then peel and grate with large grater.
Add 1 tsp. salt and mix slightly.
Melt 1/2 cube butter.
Remove from heat and add diluted soup, sour cream, green onions and grated cheese.
Fold this mixture with potatoes.
Place in buttered casserole and cover top with cornflake crumbs.
Bake in oven at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: jello salad
directions: Let jello almost set, then whip.
Add 1 cup whipped cottage cheese.
Add 1 cup drained pineapple and mix.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: grandma's smothered chicken
directions: * I use fatback grease, it is better.

title: misty chicken
directions: Mix together first four ingredients and heat until thick. Then add the next four ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Spray a 9 x 9-inch pan or oblong dish.

title: breakfast brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet over medium heat until done. Drain in colander.
Combine with remaining ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine chicken, enchilada sauce, chicken soup, onion and garlic salt.
Line a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with about 2/3 of the tortilla chips.
Pour chicken mixture over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover with remaining tortilla chips.
Pour chicken broth over chips and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Serve with Spanish rice and refried beans.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve cocoa in boiling water and mix hot coffee with soda. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add all but baking powder and flour. Add baking powder to flour and add to creamed mixture.
Beat until flour disappears.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
May use 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 round pans.
Dust cooled cake with powdered sugar or frost with your favorite frosting.
Moist enough to enjoy without frosting.

title: gelatin flavored cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Ad gelatin (any flavor) for color.
Add dry ingredients to butter and sugar; mix well. Press dough through cookie press.
Sprinkle with gelatin.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 80 cookies.

title: date balls
directions: Mix egg, sugar, margarine and dates in saucepan.
Cook until dates are soft and mixture is thick.
Place saucepan in ice water until mix is cool enough to handle.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts and mix quickly.
Shape into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Break lettuce into bowl until half full.
Add in layers celery, onion, green peppers, peas, cheese and bacon.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise together.
Pour over salad.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown meat over medium-high heat about 5 minutes, stirring to break up chunks.
Drain off fat.
Stir in salsa and beans.
Bring to a simmer; cover and cook 25 to 30 minutes, stirring often, until flavors are blended.
Makes 3 cups.

title: oriental pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into diagonal strips about 1/4 x 2-inches.
Preheat large skillet; sprinkle salt into skillet.
Brown meat.
Mix garlic, ginger, sugar and soy sauce; stir into meat.
Cover. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add onion and bean sprouts.
Cover and simmer for 5 more minutes.
Make a smooth paste of cornstarch and reserved liquid; stir slowly into hot mixture and cook until liquid thickens.
Place green peppers and tomatoes on top.
Cover; steam 3 minutes or until peppers are cooked tender-crisp.
Serve over rice (broccoli can be substituted for bean sprouts).

title: hot sausage and cheese pinwheels
directions: Unroll crescent rolls, leaving in rectangles.
Spread sausage evenly and sprinkle generously with
cheese.
Roll into logs. Chill until firm.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool about 20 minutes.
Slice into 4 to 5 slices per roll.
Serve with mustard.
Serves 6.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix together mushroom soup, celery soup and milk.
Put uncooked rice in bottom of 8 x 11-inch dish.
Layer turkey next. Pour soup mixture over and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese dessert
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add syrup; cool slightly.

title: mom's bread pudding
directions: Heat milk to scalding (bubbles around edge of pan).
Pour milk over bread cubes.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate soda
directions: For each serving, pour syrup and milk into a chilled 14-ounce or 16-ounce glass; mix well.
Add chilled carbonated water to fill glass 3/4 full.
Stir.
Add 1 to 2 scoops vanilla ice cream.
Fill to top with carbonated water.

title: norwegian toast cookies(tebrod)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given.
Dough should be sticky, but not real glossy.
You may have to add a tablespoon or so more flour.
On a greased cookie sheet, spoon and shape into 3 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven; slice loaves.
Arrange slices, cut side down, on cookie sheet and bake another 15 minutes at 375° or until golden brown.
Each loaf makes 18 slices.
To make daintier slices, make loaves larger or narrower.
These are very good.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until almost tender.
Drain. Arrange on bottom of greased casserole.
Lay boned chicken breasts on top.
Mix mayo, soup and lemon juice and pour over chicken. Bake 30 minutes at 350° and then turn off oven.
Lay sliced Cheddar cheese on top and leave in oven until melted.

title: ground beef grandstyle
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Combine softened cream cheese, soup and milk.
Add salt, ketchup and hamburger.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in a 2 qt. casserole dish and bake uncovered at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.
Place biscuits on top and bake 15-20 minutes longer or until golden brown.

title: anzac cookies(australian-new zealand army corps)
directions: Melt margarine and syrup.
Add to dry ingredients.
Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Add to other ingredients.
Place on greased cookie sheet by teaspoon size.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican spiced bean salad
directions: Prepare dressing according to package directions; and set aside.
Open and drain all beans and corn.
Toss together in a large bowl with sliced onions.
Toss again with dressing and let it set for at least one or more hours.

title: hot cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in an ovenproof dish and heat at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Plump raisins by soaking in boiling water. Soak them, covered, for 30 minutes. Drain and allow to dry.
In a large bowl, combine raisins, peanuts, onion, bacon and broccoli.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, brown sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli. Mix well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Blend oatmeal; measure and blend in a blender to a fine powder.
Cream the butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix together with the flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add chips, candy and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 minutes at 375°.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and water.
Add pudding mix.
Mix well.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture in a 2 1/2-quart serving dish.
Top with a 1/3 each wafers, bananas, pudding.
Repeat layers twice, ending with pudding.
Chill and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and
onion	together
until tender.
Season with salt, pepper and sugar
to	taste.	Mix
with
soup, sour cream and beaten egg.
Melt
butter
and	mix with stuffing in separate container.	Spread 1/3
of stuffing mixture on bottom of casserole dish.
Layer
half	of squash mixture, spread 1/3 crumbs on top of mixture,
then
rest
of squash, then rest of crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tailgate chicken wings
directions: Disjoint chicken wings and discard tips.
Stir all others together for marinade.
Marinate overnight in plastic bag, turning a few times.
To cook, place in flat pan so they can spread out and bake at 350° for more than an hour, basting with marinade until its gone and wings are glazed.
Sue cooks them about an hour and a half.

title: red cabbage simplified
directions: Prepare the cabbage.
Melt the butter and saute the onion. Add brown sugar, vinegar and caraway seed.
Add the cabbage and cook it for 25 minutes. Stir it frequently.
Canned red cabbage may be substituted.
Cook about 5 minutes.

title: oven meatballs
directions: Mix Stove Top as directed.
Chop pepper and onion and mix with stuffing.
Add A.1. sauce; mix this with raw hamburger.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spoon soup over meatballs and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: touch o spice cider
directions: In a saucepan, simmer cider, water and spices together for 10 minutes.
Serve warm, garnished with an orange slice.

title: chicken escallops
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; set aside for later.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese, set aside for later.
Open each breast and lay on waxed paper, pound flat with mallet.
Dredge with flour mixture, refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Combine egg and water, whip. Dip each floured breast in egg mixture, drain thoroughly.
Coat each with bread crumb-cheese mixture, press coating on firmly with knife blade.
Cover lightly and refrigerate 1/2 hour for coating to firm.
Heat oil in heavy skillet until bread cube sizzles gently and browns on the edges.
Fry each escallop in hot oil 4 minutes on each side or until thoroughly cooked.
Place on serving platter and drizzle with hot chicken gravy, if desired.

title: butterscotch whole wheat squares
directions: Put into 2 (8-inch) greased and dusted cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump fruit cocktail, sugar, flour, soda, salt and eggs in bowl and stir together.
Pour into prepared 9 x 13-inch or 2 round pans. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Glaze while hot.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into a 3-quart casserole. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sourdough
directions: In a bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Stir until dissolved. Blend in sugar. Add enough flour to make a pancake batter type consistency.
Make the dough the night before and let stand on counter.
Each time a portion is used, add 1 cup water and flour to make same consistency.
Use recipe to make biscuits or cinnamon rolls.

title: dill dip for veggies
directions: Stir together; let sit overnight to let flavors soak through. Serve with all types of raw veggies.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, egg, parsley, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup soup.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape in about 20 small balls and place in skillet.
Mix remaining soup, water and Worcestershire. Pour over meatballs.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes, stirring often.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: lemon lust
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and confectioners sugar until soft and creamy.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix milk and pudding mix.
Spoon over top and spread out.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: "spoonbreaker" chocolate chip cookies(ask greg how these got their name!)
directions: Grind oatmeal and Hershey bar (broken into small pieces) in food processor or blender until oatmeal resembles coarse flour.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix well, then add chips and nuts.
Put spoonfuls 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°. Makes 9 to 10 dozen.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: chocolate supreme
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine together like pie crust and pat firmly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken and ham bake
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Place ham in casserole dish.
Place chicken over ham.
Mix sour cream, soup and cheese. Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 300° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook butter, sugar and water on high until color of brown grocery bag, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay Hershey bars on top.
After they melt, spread out.
Cut or break into serving pieces.

title: dump fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into a bowl and slice bananas into it. Let set for 10 minutes, then drain.
Drain 1 can of oranges. Combine all fruits and mix.
Chill.

title: bacon chestnuts
directions: Make a day ahead to marinate.
Wrap each chestnut in 1/2 slice bacon; lay in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain fat.
Then mix and pour over the following: brown sugar, granulated sugar and catsup.
Refrigerate overnight and then bake again for 30 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.

title: m's pineapple pie
directions: Mix pineapple, cornstarch, sugar and salt. Cook until clear and thick, stirring constantly. Take off heat and add butter and lemon juice.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: aunt kate's poppy seed bread
directions: Knead until dough leaves your hands.
Form into 9 balls.
Roll each ball out on floured board and spread with poppy seed filling. Roll up.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: campers hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly. Store in tightly covered container.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Line casserole dish with chips.
Add meat, beans, taco seasoning and water, mixed.
Add Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes to melt cheese.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
In saucepan, simmer milk, butter, Cheez Whiz and sharp cheeses, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese. Continue stirring until Mozzarella is partly melted.
Pour mixture into casserole dish.
Break up bread into pieces over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop with teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
This recipe is 100 years old!!!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients, let come to a boil.
When cool, dip pieces of chicken in sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken. It can be used on pork also.
Recipe will cover one.
Cover and cook at 350° for 2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: In a large pot, combine the dry beans and enough water to cover them.
Soak overnight.
Bring beans and water to a boil; boil for 2 minutes, then remove pot from heat.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Combine beans and juice with remaining ingredients.
Put this mixture into a casserole.
Cover.
Bake 5 hours at 300°.
If liquid evaporates, add more water.

title: crisp crusted baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Set aside.
Beat egg and milk in a bowl.
In another bowl, mix potato flakes, garlic powder and cheese.
Roll chicken first in egg mix, then in the potato flake mixture.
Melt butter in a shallow baking pan.
Roll coated chicken pieces in the butter and place skin side up in a pan. Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until juices from thighs run clear when pierced with a fork.

title: diabetic strawberry shortcake
directions: Cook cake according to directions, adding 1 to 2 teaspoons strawberry flavoring.
Put in a square baking dish (8 or 9-inch size).
When cool, cut in half, then split layers.
Mix whipped topping according to directions.
Add 2 teaspoons strawberry flavoring.

title: dave's midwest chili
directions: Chop onion into 1/4-inch pieces.
Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add ground beef-onion mixture to beans and tomatoes in a 2 1/2-quart crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Stir sugar, butter, milk and salt together; bring to a boil. Stir constantly until soft ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat; immediately add chocolate chips and Marshmallow Fluff.
Keep stirring until everything is dissolved.
Add nuts, if desired. Pour immediately into buttered pan; cut when lukewarm or when knife cuts cleanly.

title: indonesian pork butt roast
directions: Brown pork butt in its own fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over meat and cover.
Simmer, turning meat 2 or 3 times, for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until very tender.
Remove meat to platter.
Slice and serve with plain or curried rice and applesauce.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat oil and eggs together.
Add sugar and vanilla; mix well. Blend in flour and cinnamon.
Add apples and nuts and mix well. Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Cut franks in 1-inch pieces.
Melt jelly, mustard and bourbon over medium heat; stir in franks.
Simmer until franks are cooked and sauce is thickened slightly.
Serve in a chafing dish.

title: aunt adele's pickles
directions: Mix brine ingredients together, bring to boil and cool.

title: crabbies
directions: Melt butter; stir in ingredients.
Spread mixture on top of English muffins.
Broil until slightly crispy and bubbly.
Cut into fourths.

title: 100% parmesan bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix cheese, margarine and Italian seasoning.
Spread on each slice of bread.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
This is a great way to doctor up stale bread.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees (325 glass pan). Microwave chocolate and butter in a large bowl on high until melted. Stir in sugar and cocoa until well blended. Mix in egg beaters and vanilla until well blended. Stir in flour until blended. Spread in greased, foil line 13 x 9 baking pan. Bake 30-35 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.

title: desert rat rabbit
directions: Cut your rabbit up as you would chicken.
Unless you've got a young one, under 4 pounds, throw the hind legs to your dog (bone the meat first, rabbit bones are brittle and could hurt your old buddy).
The reason for this is that the hind legs of an adult jackrabbit are so gamey and strong that no amount of kitchen trickery will render them edible.
Wash the pieces and set them to soak overnight in a gallon of salt water with a 1/2 cup of vinegar.
Pour off the salt water and rinse.
Cover with cold water and bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and let simmer as slowly as possible for at least an hour.
Remove from water and let cool.
Put some seasoned flour in a paper bag and drop in rabbit pieces and shake until flour covers them.
Heat a little bacon grease or other oil in a big iron skillet.
Brown both sides of rabbit at high heat; reduce heat to low simmer.
Add a little water and cover skillet so rabbit will steam.
Should be done in about 30 minutes to an hour.
Poke with a fork to check tenderness.
Serve like fried chicken.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in casserole dish.
Layer pork chops on top of rice. Pour soup over casserole.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook until boiling.
Fold in handful of marshmallows in hot sauce.
Set overnight.
Prepare whipping cream as directed.
Crush up peanuts.
Then layer bananas, sauce and nuts.
Repeat and layer until bowl is full.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Spray a 9 X 13 pan. Put rice on bottom. Mix together soup mix, soup and water. Cover with foil and bake at 400 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Suggestion:
You can freeze leftovers for up to 30 days.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In a saucepan boil margarine, water and cocoa.
Pour this while hot over dry ingredients (flour, sugar and salt).
In a bowl beat buttermilk, vanilla, soda and eggs.
Add to first mixture. Bake in a large greased cake pan or jelly roll pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting while cake is warm.

title: "garbage" salsa for chili
directions: Steam green beans seven minutes only.
Run cold water over them to stop the cooking.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Cook flour, butter and milk until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Prepare 1/2 package of the stuffing mix, using water and butter as directed.
Add onion and celery.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ham, cheese, broccoli and soup in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir remaining ingredients until dough forms. Drop by spoonfuls evenly over broccoli mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 to 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: deer jerky
directions: Marinate deer strips (1/8-inch thick) for 2 days.
Use dehydrator or 170° oven (place on racks with toothpicks until dry or right consistency).

title: mary's cheese cake
directions: Chill milk in freezer until milk just starts to crystallize. Add water to gelatine and Jell-O and refrigerate until edge of Jell-O is thick.
Whip cream cheese and sugar together and set aside.
Melt butter; add to crumbs and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Whip the chilled milk until thick like whipping cream.
Fold in cream cheese mixture.
Add gelatine.
On low speed, blend entire mixture until everything folds in.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling or sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Pour cranberry juice, pineapple juice, water and brown sugar into a 20-cup percolator.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Place remaining ingredients in percolator basket.
Perk through complete cycle.
Serve hot.
Makes 16 cups.

title: easy italian casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion.
Drain and mix with the other ingredients, except cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, green onions, Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, Accent and 1/3 of the dried beef, mixing well.
Form into a ball.
Lay rest of beef on wax paper or foil.
Roll cheese ball in the beef to form outer coating.
Chill in refrigerator and serve with party crackers.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion over medium heat until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat eggs, milk and baking mix until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan; stir in flour until lightly brown.
Gradually add broth.
Blend in cheese and stir until melted.
Saute vegetables in remaining butter until translucent; cool slightly and puree in processor or blender. Soup may be made ahead to this point.
At serving time combine cheese mixture with puree and heat gently.
Add cream and seasonings; continue to heat gently and adjust seasoning.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dessert pizza (fruit)
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and pour over baked cookie dough.

title: noodles
directions: Mix together and roll thin.
Let dry a little and cut.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger with taco seasoning.
Add beans; break chips. Add all ingredients and mix well with dressing and Tabasco sauce. Mix in large bowl.

title: icebox slaw
directions: Boil the vinegar, vegetable oil, celery seed and salt and pour over cabbage, onions, bell pepper and sugar.
Put in refrigerator. This will keep in refrigerator for 3 weeks.

title: blitz torte
directions: Cream shortening; beat in sugar and salt.
Add beaten egg yolks, vanilla, milk and flour sifted with baking powder.
Spread mixture in two round layer cake pans, greased (this will barely cover bottom of pans).
Beat egg whites until very light; add 3/4 cup sugar gradually.
Spread meringue over batter in both pans. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Put together with Cream Filling.
Makes 1 (9-inch) layer cake.

title: orange or lime salad
directions: Stir Jell-O and pineapple together.
Add sour cream, Cool Whip and nuts.
Stir well.
Will be ready to eat.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine milk and egg.
Add Bisquick, parsley, onion and half the cheese.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on batter.
Pour melted butter over top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Cut top off tomatoes and put on baking sheet.
Sprinkle lightly with crumbs and dot with butter.
Broil until heated and lightly browned on top (or bake tomatoes in hot oven, 425°, for about 10 minutes).
Sometimes I use fresh bread cubes.
Melt the butter in a very small pan and add bread cubes, stirring, until butter is absorbed.
Then place the bread cubes on top of the tomatoes.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Cut foil to wrap 1 potato per person.
Wash potatoes.
Slice the potatoes about 1/4-inch slices all the way through.

title: chicken ala prego
directions: Beat egg. Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese together.

Dip chicken in egg, then in the crumbs. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan; put some sauce on bottom of pan. Place chicken on top of sauce. Put remaining sauce on top of chicken. Bake covered 1 hour at 400°. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and melt in oven.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop.
Cook about 5 minutes at 375°.

title: rainbow pasta dinner
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook pasta until just tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain, then rinse with cold water and drain again.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients except lettuce to pasta.
Toss to blend well.
Serve at room temperature or chilled on a bed of shredded lettuce.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, mustard, brown sugar and garlic powder into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken wings; coat well.
Marinate 2 hours or more.
Bake in same pan for 1 hour at 375°.
Baste while baking.

title: waffles or pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Add egg yolks and milk, slowly beating it until batter is smooth.
Add melted butter and stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Drain well.
Add all other ingredients and spaghetti.
Simmer about 1/2 hour.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and crushed pineapple well.
Mix Eagle Brand milk with cream cheese well.
Add lemon juice or Real Lemon. Blend well.
Add Cool Whip with electric mixer.
Stir in nuts and coconut with large spoon.
Refrigerate.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
In another skillet, cook hamburger with onion and mushrooms until done.
Drain off.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer about 15 minutes.
Add to spaghetti with Parmesan cheese.
Mix well in a casserole dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cook until cheese is turning light brown in a moderate oven.

title: cheddar carousel
directions: Combine all ingredients, except preserves.
Put in ring mold. Chill thoroughly.
(Mixture will form together when chilled.) Unmold and fill center with preserves.

title: nutty cracker delights
directions: Place crackers in a single layer in a foil lined 15 x 10-inch baking pan. Melt butter. Add sugar and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cook for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour evenly over crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle chocolate chips and spread when chips melt.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and gently pat into chocolate. Cool in refrigerator for a few hours. Break into pieces.

title: chicken san angelo
directions: Dredge chicken in flour and set aside.
Heat oil in pan and add garlic and chicken.
Brown chicken on both sides and season. Pour off oil and deglaze pan with white wine and chicken stock. Add broccoli, artichoke hearts, sun-dried tomatoes and roasted red peppers.
Reduce liquid in pan by cooking until sauce is of the consistency you want.
Add in softened butter and serve over pasta or rice.

title: pickled pears
directions: Bring almost to a boil.
Drop pears into mixture for 5 to 10 minutes.
Check with ice pick for tenderness.
As soon as you can stick ice pick through pears, put in jars and seal.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate the potatoes and onions (if you are using them) with the grating disk of food processor or using the large holes of a hand-held grater.
Transfer the potatoes and onions to a colander. Squeeze mixture to press out as much liquid as possible. Transfer to bowl.
Mix in the egg, salt, pepper, flour and baking powder.

title: honey nut crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, mix cereal, oats, nuts, cinnamon and salt.
In small saucepan, mix butter, honey and brown sugar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until butter is melted and ingredients are well blended.
Pour honey and butter mixture over cereal; mix until thoroughly coated.
Spread into 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until mixture is golden brown, turning occasionally.
Immediately spread mixture onto waxed paper.
Stir in raisins.
Cool completely.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: donna's chocolate logs
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine.
Let it cool well.
Add marshmallows and nuts and mix well.
Tear off 3 pieces of aluminum foil.
Divide chocolate into 3 parts and spread on foil.
Roll it up; sprinkle coconut on candy as you roll them up.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut in slices.

title: top of the stove cookies
directions: Add together margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Have ready peanut butter, vanilla and pinch of salt.
Add to boiling syrup and mix.
Add oats, 1 cup at a time, mixing thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper until cold.

title: lemon fish fillets
directions: Dot
each
fillet with butter and lightly sprinkle with salt. Broil about 3 minutes on each side.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Make jello as directed.
Let it sit awhile but not until firm. Mix strawberries, jello and Cool Whip.
Put cake pieces in pan. Pour jello mixture over the cake and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: chinese noodle-link sausage
directions: Cook
noodles
and drain.
Fry sausage in small pieces. Leave about 3 tablespoons fat in pan. Fry onion slightly.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place
in
2	quart casserole. Top with cheese. Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: praline pie
directions: Bake crust 5 minutes.
Add margarine, brown sugar and nuts. Put back in oven and bake 10 more minutes.
Let cool. Cover with vanilla pudding mix.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Blend with butter.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Add buttermilk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: delicious pecan oat cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand.
Mix sifted flour and baking powder and set aside.
Cream butter, brown sugar and flavoring well.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with oatmeal. Add nuts.
Spoon in paper baking cups in muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes.
Makes 20 to 24.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, saute onion, celery and carrots in butter over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth. Cover
and simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients and seasonings; gradually
stir
in
milk.
Add
milk
mixture to vegetables
and broth mixture.
Cover and simmer gently until thickened.
Cut cheese
into
chunks.
Add
to
soup mixture. Heat over very low heat, stirring constantly just until cheese is melted.

title: old time ketchup
directions: Put the spices in spice bag.
Cook until thick.
May add 2 or 3 tablespoons cornstarch last for more thickness.

title: apple ann cake
directions: Mix and pour into an oblong greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Sprinkle top with sugar.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Beat well.
Line muffin tins with papers.
Put a vanilla wafer in the bottom of each paper.
Put 3 tablespoons of ingredients on each wafer.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling.
Makes 24 tarts.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Dredge in seasoned flour.
Melt shortening and brown meat on both sides.
Add onion, celery, green pepper, tomato soup and water.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
If desired, thicken gravy with cornstarch dissolved in water.

title: southwest white chili
directions: Heat olive oil in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add chicken; cook 4 to 6 minutes stirring often.
Remove chicken with slotted spoon.
Cover and keep warm.
Add chopped onion to saucepan.
Cook 2 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth, green chilies, garlic powder, ground cumin, oregano leaves, cilantro and ground red pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in cooked chicken and kidney beans.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Garnish with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash avocado with lemon juice and mix in rest of ingredients (may blend all ingredients but avocado and lemon juice).
Chill but serve at room temperature.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Combine oats, flour and sugar.
Mix in Parkay butter until mixture is crumbly.
Place half of mixture on the bottom of a buttered pan.
Spoon in pie filling on top of bottom mixture. Spread the remaining over the top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until lightly brown.
Serve warm.

title: turkey pasta salad
directions: Stir together macaroni, turkey, celery and red pepper in large bowl.
Stir together cream cheese, sour cream and milk.
Add to macaroni.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Crumble half cake in bottom of large bowl.
Prepare pudding mix adding 1/2 cup extra milk.
Layer with 1/2 cup of pineapple and 1/2 can pie filling.
Cover with layer of Cool Whip and nuts.
Repeat with remaining cake, pineapple and pie filling.

title: chicken kabobs
directions: You will also need 12 (6-inch) long skewers.
On each skewer, alternate chicken, green pepper and apple.
Repeat once.
Place kabobs in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine lemon juice with oil.
Brush on kabobs.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper and salt. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stir-fried green beans
directions: Wash and string beans.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Pour oil around top of preheated wok, allow to heat for 2 minutes.
Add beans.
Stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth and sugar.
Cover. Reduce heat and cook 10 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and water; add to wok.
Cook beans until thickened.
Yields 4 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs and milk.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla, oleo and bananas.
Line bowl with wafers or cook in microwave on High for 3 minutes then stir.
Continue until it thickens.

title: two layer fruit cake
directions: Boil sweet milk, sugar, flour and eggs.
Cook until thick and then add chopped nuts, raisins, coconut and vanilla.
Then add candied fruit.

title: guacamole(mexican dip)
directions: Cut avocados in half and remove seeds.
With a fork, mash avocado flesh with onion and garlic until smooth.
Blend in lemon juice and oil.
Season to taste with salt, black pepper, cayenne and the sauces.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar.
Blend eggs and milk.
Add to sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Cool.
Stir in 1 cup graham cracker crumbs, nuts and chocolate chips.
Line bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Spread mixture over crackers.
Top with another layer of whole graham crackers.
Spread with frosting and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; fold in chocolate chips last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a large, deep skillet, heat butter.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic; saute 6 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in flour.
Gradually add 2 1/2 cups of water, stirring until smooth.
Return to heat.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook, covered, stirring occasionally, for about 30 minutes, until rice is tender.

title: peppered rice casserole
directions: Cook rice with salt according to the directions on package. Grease casserole dish with butter.
Layer the ingredients:
1/2 the rice, 1/2 the sour cream, 1/2 the chilies and 1/2 the cheese. Repeat the layers.
Dot the top with the butter.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with tinfoil. Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: picnic cookies
directions: Place sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine in large saucepan. Cook over heat until bubbly; stir often.
Stir in oats and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add peanut butter and 2 beaten eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, then roll in small balls and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Then press down with a fork.
Bake 10 minutes in 350° oven or until golden brown.

title: easy cheesy spaghetti bake
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add water, tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix and boil gently, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Stir often. Cook 3/4 pound spaghetti.
Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add flour, gradually, and instant dry milk that has been mixed with water to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Add American cheese and Parmesan cheese and cook until cheese melts.
Layer in baking dish as follows:
1/2 spaghetti, 1/2 sauce, cheese sauce, remaining spaghetti and remaining sauce.
Top with 1/4 cup American cheese. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: turkey or chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Arrange in greased baking dish. Layer poultry on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over poultry.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs over it; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until it bubbles.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Thaw spinach and drain. Chop artichoke hearts into tiny pieces. Melt butter or margarine. Combine all ingredients and refrigerate or serve warm, not hot.

title: floyd's chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix as any cake.
Bake in 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
Cook at 300° for 80 minutes or until done.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together.
Put 3/4 of oatmeal mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook last five ingredients together. Pour cooked rhubarb over oatmeal mixture.
Top with remaining oatmeal mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, cool and cut into bars.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly grease a (9-inch) spring-form pan.
Mix crumbs with cinnamon, 1/2 cup sugar and butter.
Press crumbs over bottom and sides of pan.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Potatoes should be defrosted.
Drop in boiling water for 3 or 4 minutes.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with 2 cups crushed corn flakes with 1/4 cup melted margarine before baking.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water and let dissolve.
Add shortening, sugar and flour.
Mix together.
Knead and roll and cut out.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake as directed.
Cool and crumble 1/2 on bottom of bowl.
Mix 1 box of pudding as directed and pour over cake.
Put 1 can of cherry pie filling over pudding.
Pour juice from pineapple in a bowl.
Use 1/2 can of pineapple over cherries. Dip bananas in juice and place on top.
Repeat steps and let set overnight in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, top with Cool Whip.
Makes 1 punch bowl or 2 large bowls full.

title: white chocolate haystacks
directions: Line baking sheet with waxed paper.
Melt the chocolate in top of double boiler over simmering water, stirring until smooth and creamy.
Add the nuts and pretzels, stirring until well coated with chocolate.
Remove the pan from heat.
Spoon the mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls onto the prepared baking sheet.
Cool to room temperature or refrigerate.
Makes 32.
The cookies may be refrigerated indefinitely.

title: blueberry nut bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Stir in milk and oil or margarine which has been melted.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture with vanilla.
Fold in blueberries and nut meats.
Bake in a greased bread pan at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Remove to rack to cool for 20 minutes; remove from pan to finish cooling.
Quick breads generally slice better if set overnight.

title: southern angel biscuits(regular recipe)
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water; set aside.
In a medium mixing bowl, mix 3 1/2 cups of flour with other dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Stir in buttermilk, yeast mixture and egg; blend thoroughly.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface; knead slightly, adding remaining flour, if necessary.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter, dipping cutter into flour as needed.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet; let dough rise slightly.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
about 24 biscuits.

title: creamy tomato soup
directions: Blend cream cheese with soup to make a smooth mixture.
Stir in water, Worcestershire sauce and celery and salt.
Heat on simmer until hot, stirring often.

title: groundhog
directions: Clean groundhog.
Parboil in clear water until tender.
Season with spices and roast over open flame.
Or bake in oven until brown.

title: creamy banana pudding(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine Eagle Brand and water; add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart round glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of the vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish as desired with wafers, etc. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: orange-pineapple molded salad
directions: Blend together the Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Fold in dry the orange Jell-O.
Fold in oranges and pineapple.
Set in mold overnight.

title: cheesy herb bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet.
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Unroll crescent dough into 2 long rectangles.
Press together perforation to seal.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over each rectangle.
Starting at shortest side, roll up jelly roll style.
Pinch edges to seal; place sections together on a cookie sheet creating one long roll.
With a knife dipped in water, partially cut each roll into 6 slices within 1/8-inch of bottom (do not cut through).
Fold down slices, alternately from left to right and overlapping slightly to form a loaf.

title: mother's cheese wafers
directions: Have margarine and cheese at room temperature.
Blend margarine and cheese together.
Add flour, salt and cayenne pepper.
Roll out to desired thickness and cut in shapes or put through a cookie press.
Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: quick reese's cup candy
directions: Use shallow pan about 8 x 11-inch size.
Melt peanut butter and margarine together.
Mix in powdered sugar; work until blended well.
Spread in pan.
Melt chocolate bar in double boiler. Spread on top of peanut mixture.
Cool 1/2 hour.
Cut and serve.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add extracts, flavoring and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder; add to mixture alternately with sour cream.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until done.
Glaze, if desired.

title: spiced carrot soup
directions: Saute the onion in the butter until softened.
Add the carrots and ginger and cook an additional 2 minutes.
Add the soup stock and simmer for 15 minutes.
Whirl in a blender or processor until fairly smooth.
Add the juices and cinnamon, then blend again. Chill.
Garnish with orange peel and a mint sprig if desired. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sauteed veal chops
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper. Brown slowly on both sides, about 20 minutes.
Remove chops; place on serving plates.
Add wine and some of prepared gravy (to thicken and taste).
Bring to a boil, scraping loose all the brown particles from skillet.
Lower heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Spoon juices over meat.
Enjoy.

title: carrots and cheese casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Saute onion and celery in a little butter.
On low heat, melt butter and Velveeta cheese.
Pour cheese mixture over vegetable mixture and stir until well mixed. Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: monkey cake
directions: You will need a tube pan with a solid bottom.

title: russian dressing(from overrock inn)
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: cape cod muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Do not overmix, a little lumpy is fine.
Pour into a paper lined or greased cupcake pan.
Sprinkle the tops with sugar and bake 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 6 small muffins or 3 large muffins.

title: taco casserole
directions: Grease a square baking dish.
In baking dish, mix Bisquick and water and spread in bottom.
Brown ground beef, drain and add seasoning.
Spread on top of Bisquick mixture. Top with onion, lettuce and tomato.
Mix sour cream and mayo and spread on top. Top with cheddar cheese and sprinkle with paprika.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave.
Add all at once the remaining ingredients.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Let set, cut into squares.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and brown sugar beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add all other ingredients, except the ginger ale which is added to the punch bowl as needed.

title: sausage and mushrooms
directions: Cook and cool sausage.
Slice when cold.
Slice onions, green peppers and celery thin.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Put in a crock-pot and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours until celery and onions are done.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel and core the apples. Make

a syrup of the water, sugar and cinnamon drops. When syrup starts to boil, drop apple halves in syrup and cook 10 to 15 minutes. When tender, place apple halves in baking dish. Pour syrup over apples and bake at 350° until done (until syrup is thick). If apples are sour, use more sugar. Cook 30 or 40 minutes in oven.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Place pork chops into roaster.
Cover with onion rings, carrot slices, pineapple, green pepper and garlic.
Mix brown sugar, vinegar, ketchup and soy sauce; pour over pork chops.
Cook at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove pork chops, vegetables and pineapple from liquid.
Mix cornstarch and pineapple juice into the pan.
Cook until thick and pour over pork chops.
Serve with rice.

title: snicker apple salad
directions: Blend together brown sugar and softened cream cheese. Stir in Cool Whip.
Add cubed apples, chopped peanuts and candy bars.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into baking dish.
Top with pats of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shortcake dessert
directions: Make pudding according to package directions.
Mix strawberries and glaze.
Layer cake, pudding, cake, strawberries, etc.
Put in glass dish where you can see layers.
Top with whipped topping.

title: shake and bake
directions: Just stir and store in refrigerator.

title: uncle terry's cole slaw
directions: Coarsely grate cabbage.
Add chopped onions and enough mayo to moisten.
Add salt & pepper to taste, and hormel bacon bits. Mix and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ribbon jello mold
directions: Let plain gelatin soften in cold water.
Boil milk with sugar. Add gelatin; let cool a little and add vanilla and sour cream. Beat well and keep warm.
Take each package of Jell-O and mix with 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Put 1 cup sour cream mixture between Jell-O. Let set after each layer until jelled.
Makes 1 glass dish (9 1/2 x 14-inch).

title: peach cake
directions: *Use water if fresh peaches.

title: lemon dill salmon
directions: Place Salon filets on a greased broiler rack.
Combine remaining ingredients and baste filets.
Broil 4-inches from heat for 10 minutes per inch of thickness.
Baste frequently.
Do not turn.
Salmon is cooked when it flakes with a fork.
Garnish with dillweed leaf.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix milk, sugar, and salt in saucepan and boil.
Set it aside until cool.
Mix yeast, water and sugar.
It will rise, so give it room to double.
You are mixing milk mixture with yeast mixture to rise.
Then gradually sift flour into the mixture and knead until all flour is mixed.
Cover with warm towel for 1 1/2 hours.
Place on lightly floured board.
Pinch off and shape with hands dough about the size of a small egg.
Place on greased pan.
Leave space to rise and spread out.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Let this dough rise 1 1/2 hours before cooking.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Heat on stove.
Mix well.
Bring to boil and serve with or without marshmallows.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Add to flour mixture.
Add chopped nuts and milk or cherry juice.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Cut cherries in half.
Place one on top of each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: julie's custard
directions: Beat eggs, add to milk slowly.
Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then 350° for 30 minutes.
This does not need to be put in a pan of water.

title: cornbread salad
directions: To cooked cornbread, add all other ingredients.
Cover and set aside for several hours.

title: coconut thins
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Mix cornstarch with flour and blend into butter and sugar mixture.
Thoroughly chill for several hours.
Shape into very small balls and roll in coconut. Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Flatten with fork and bake for 20 or 25 minutes in a 325° oven.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.
Freezes very well.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onions, milk, parsley, salt, pepper, egg and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into meatballs.
Brown meatballs in butter; remove from heat.
Heat chili and jelly, stirring constantly, until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs.

title: black bean sauce
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over moderately high heat.
Add peppers and garlic; saute 5 minutes, stirring frequently with wooden spoon.
Stir in beans and minced cilantro.

title: brunch quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese and milk in saucepan; stir over low heat until smooth.
Gradually add cream cheese mixture to eggs, mixing until blended.
Saute onion in margarine; add onion and remaining ingredients to cream cheese mixture.
Mix well. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Yields 8 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Note:
Omit baking powder and salt if using self-rising flour.

title: hamburger cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Melt cheese in double boiler or crock-pot.
Mix cheese, hamburger, Ro-Tel, chili powder and hot sauce.
Serve with chips.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Add sugar, vanilla, soda, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Fold in apples and nuts. Batter will be thick. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° about 1 hour or less.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook 10 minutes.
Add beef or pork.

title: turtle sundae cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on the box.
Put 1/2 of the batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Preheat 10-inch skillet, uncovered, over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Melt butter in the skillet, then add steak slices and onion.
Brown about 5 minutes.
Add bouillon cube and water; cover.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Add soup, mushrooms, salt and pepper, stirring to blend.
Cover and heat 10 minutes.
Add sour cream, stirring to blend.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Serve over hot cooked egg noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat
cream cheese and sugar with electric mixer.
Add 5 eggs and
2 egg yolks 1 at a time, beating after each addition. Add flour,
followed
by
heavy cream.
Add vanilla and grated rind. Mix
until
a
smooth,
creamy consistency.
Pour into a heavy aluminum
spring-form
pan.
Bake
in a 500° oven for 12 minutes. Reduce
heat
to 250° and bake for 1 hour.
Yields 16 servings.

title: pudding salad
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix jello and puddings with water together; bring to a full boil and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool completely.
When cooled, add Cool Whip and fruit cocktail.

title: orange pecans
directions: Put sugar and orange juice in large saucepan and cook to a soft ball stage on candy thermometer (236° to 240°).
Turn off heat and add orange rind and pecans.
Use a wooden spoon; stir until mixture turns cream color (5 to 7 minutes). Pour onto cookie sheet; spread out.
When cool enough to handle, break apart.

title: cinnamon balls
directions: Roll into small balls about 1/2 size of a walnut.
Roll into cinnamon sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats and drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Let sit in refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Combine egg yolks, juice of lemons, sugar, cream and salt in double boiler and cook until custardy.
Stir constantly.
Chill, then add whipped cream, pineapple, cherries, almonds and green grapes.
Chill for 24 hours and garnish with whipped cream and grated coconut.

title: strawberries devonshire
directions: Wash and hull strawberries.
Place in large serving bowl. Cover and chill.
Just before serving, combine sour cream and brown sugar in a small bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Serve over strawberries.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle lean pork chops with salt and pepper.
In 10-inch skillet, brown in tablespoon of hot shortening.
Pour off drippings.
In baking dish, pour around chops a mixture of mushroom soup, milk and water.
