Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Stir gravy well.

title: walnut chews
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, nuts, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: sausage rice bake
directions: In shallow 2-quart casserole, place rice; set aside.
In large skillet on medium heat, saute sausage, stirring to crumble. Drain; discard excess fat.
In same skillet, mix celery, onions, pepper and sausage.
Cook until veggies are tender and onions are transparent.
Stir in salt, pepper and broth.
Increase heat and boil mixture 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine mix with rice.
Cover dish with tight fitting lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until rice absorbs liquid and is tender.
To serve, fluff rice; sprinkle with pecan halves.
Serves 6.

title: bay-lans cream of potato soup
directions: In large pot, cook the potatoes, celery and carrots in the chicken broth until tender.
Mash the vegetables with a fork coarsely.
Add the processed cheese and stir over medium heat until melted.
Add the milk and stir again.
Do not let the mixture boil.
Add seasoning, parsley and green onions; cook on low heat 20 minutes.

title: cream blueberry muffins
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, sugar and sour cream.	Combine flour, salt, baking powder and
baking
soda
and	add
to egg mixture. Mix well.
Dust
blueberries
with the 2 tablespoons flour and carefully fold into
batter.
Bake	at
for 24 minutes in greased or sprayed muffin tins.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: orange buttermilk salad
directions: In a large pan, bring pineapple to a boil; remove from heat. Stir in Jell-O.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in buttermilk. Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour into mold or Pyrex oblong dish.
Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix milk with thawed lemonade.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Put in pie shell.
Chill 1 hour.

title: memphis corn fritters
directions: Sift the flour; measure and resift with the baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat egg, then add milk and shortening, then flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Fold in corn and let stand 5 to 10 minutes while you heat shortening.
Fry at 360° and serve hot.

title: el rancho casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: grandma's peanut brittle
directions: Bring sugar, Karo syrup, water and butter to boil.
Add peanuts and boil until peanuts get brown (20 minutes).
Remove from heat and add vanilla; mix well.
Fold in baking soda and pour on three buttered cookie sheets.
Pull out as it cools.

title: stuffed burgers
directions: Preheat broiler.
Shape beef into 12 thin patties.
In small bowl, combine mustard and olives.
Place 1 tablespoon of mixture in center of each of 6 patties.
Top with remaining patties. Pinch edges together to seal.
Place patties on greased rack in broiler pan.
Broil 8 minutes or until done.
Toast buns.
Serve burgers in buns.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt together peanut butter and margarine.
Stir in powdered sugar; add vanilla if desired and add a few drops of milk (enough to make it like fudge).
Press in pan.
Refrigerate.
(Can add nuts if desired.)

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and baking soda; add oil, eggs, buttermilk and vanilla flavor.
Blend until smooth.
Add bananas and nuts and mix well.
Grease pan; bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: You will also need 12 cupcake liners.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Soak fruit and raisins in the brandy at least 12 hours.
Mix together the flour, baking soda, cloves (or allspice) and cinnamon; set aside.

title: instant lemon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Using electric mixer, combine butter and egg.
Mix in cake mix and lemon juice.
Batter will be very thick.
Mix in Rice Krispies using beater or by hand.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 8 minutes.
Do not brown.
Let cool briefly, then remove to surface covered with paper towel.
Store in covered container.

title: mom's best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Blend remaining ingredients.
(For a softer, rounder cookie, add 1/2 cup flour.)
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: bernaise sauce
directions: Stir egg yolks, lemon and wine vigorously in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Add 1/4 cup butter.
Heat over very low heat, stirring constantly until butter is melted and sauce is thickened.
Stir in onion, tarragon and chervil leaves.
Serve with fish or steak. Yields 3/4 cup of sauce.

title: pete's hamburger pie(a variation)
directions: Grease 9-inch square pan.
Put in pizza dough, covering sides. Brown hamburger, drain.
Mix in sauce, pour into pan.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and is brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar, raisins, egg yolks, salt and cinnamon in a large saucepan.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Pour into pie crust.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Jell-O, oil and eggs.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Add strawberries and mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Frost with vanilla icing.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix melted butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In small bowl, beat other 1/2 cup butter about 30 seconds, until softened.
Add powdered sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Spread egg mixture over crumb mixture. Slice bananas; arrange over egg mixture.
Spoon pineapple over bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with shaved chocolate and nuts.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Cut into squares.
Top with cherries if desired.

title: fruit kabobs
directions: Take your pretzel stick and put on a piece of cheese, slice of banana and a pineapple chunk.
Serve and eat.
Kids can do this!

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature.
Mix well; shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cut in serving pieces or punch holes in cake while hot.
Mix milk and cream of coconut.
Pour over cake while hot.
Cool and cover.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with coconut.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In skillet, saute hamburger meat about 5 minutes.
In the meantime, put about 4 or 6 cups water and vegetables in a pan and bring to a boil.
Drain meat and add to vegetable mix.
Cook until done, about 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all but coconut in blender, low speed, for 3 minutes. (Can use medium speed on mixer for 3 minutes.)
Pour into greased pie pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Make into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain grease.
Add all together.
Cook until potatoes are done.

title: hot corned beef party sandwiches
directions: Spread thin layer of mayonnaise and desired amount of mustard on each half.

title: clam dip
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Add clams, catsup, cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine skim milk, flour, yogurt and tomatoes with green chilies in saucepan.
Heat over medium heat, stirring often, until thickened.
If too thick, thin with chicken stock.
In skillet, heat oil.
Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Add diced chicken and heat through.
In casserole dish, make layers of sauce, chicken mixture, tortilla quarters and cheese, ending with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add dry mixture.
Add eggs and sour cream; beat well.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: zucchini nut bread(makes 2 loaves; tasty)
directions: Beat eggs gradually, adding sugar until well mixed.
Add vegetable oil and beat.
Mix together flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
To egg mixture, add the zucchini alternating with dry mixture.
Add raisins, apples, carrots, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 55 minutes or until bread is done. Cool about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
May freeze up to 6 months.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Slice carrots crosswise on the bias about 1-inch thick.
Cook, covered, in boiling salted water until just tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Combine sour cream, cottage cheese and spices.
Fold in potatoes, pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Season roast and roll into flour, coating roast.
Brown in hot skillet with a little oil on both sides until just brown.
Put roast into crock-pot.
Pour can of soup over roast and sprinkle about 1 teaspoon of Worcestershire sauce on top.
Put top on and cook on low all day, about 6 to 8 hours.
Makes a delicious gravy.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in water with 1/2 teaspoon of salt and pepper until done (approximately 20 minutes).
Saute 1/2 cup onions and 1/2 cup green peppers in butter until soft.
Add Velveeta cheese, cream of mushroom soup and cream of chicken soup. When chicken is done, remove from water and boil 2 cups of noodles in chicken broth until tender.
Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces and combine with soup mixture.
Add cooked noodles with 1/4 cup broth.
Put in lightly greased baking dish and bake 30 minutes at 325° or 12 to 15 minutes in microwave.

title: soft caramel icing
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in a buttered heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often (soft ball stage) at 240° on candy thermometer.
Let cool slightly.
Add vanilla. Beat until spreading consistency.
Enjoy!
Enough for 2 layer cake.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and tortillas.
Layer in rectangular baking dish:
6 tortillas, then half of chicken mixture and half of the grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot throughout.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
Put in jars and process 20 minutes in water bath.

title: seven layer magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
in 13 x 9 inch baking pay, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter; pour Eagle Brand evenly on top of crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients in order listed; press down firmly with fork.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Chill if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: microwave fresh strawberry jam
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, place berries and pectin.
Stir well. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High 8 to 10 minutes until mixture is at full rolling boil.
Add sugar to boiling berries and stir well.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, except kisses.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Place chocolate kiss on top and press down. Bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and rub skins with oil.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until done.
Allow potatoes to stand until cool to the touch.
Slice skin away from top of each potato.
Carefully scoop out the pulp, leaving shell intact; mash pulp.
Combine potato pulp and remaining ingredients except paprika, stirring well. Stuff shells with potato mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Seal securely in aluminum foil.
Freeze.
To serve, thaw in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions, but add vegetables with seasoning package. Combine soup, milk and parsley.
Set aside.

title: italian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water. Mix well and set aside.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces. Add soups, sour cream and noodles; pour into casserole dish. Salt and pepper to taste. Cut bread into inch squares and place on top. Pour melted butter over bread. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bread is brown.

title: yogurt chicken
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a shallow dish; set aside. Brush yogurt on all sides of chicken breast halves; coat with bread crumbs mixture.
Place in a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Drizzle with butter and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Combine cocoa and food coloring to make a paste.
Stir into creamed mixture. Sift flour and salt together. Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture. Blend well; add vanilla. Combine vinegar and soda.
While still foaming, add to the batter.
Do not beat, instead stir gently. Bake in two greased and floured layer pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put rice in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole Pyrex dish.
Next, sprinkle on poultry seasoning.
Lay chicken on rice.
Pour 3 cups water on top of the chicken.
Sprinkle on salt and pepper.
Add mushroom soup last.
Cover chicken and rice with mushroom soup. Cover with aluminum foil and cook until done, 50 minutes at 400°.

title: no cook ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together, then add milk, cream and vanilla.
Beat until well mixed.
Put mixture into ice cream freezer canister and crank it until mixture gets solid.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Cook zucchini until tender and drain.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Combine egg yolks, sour cream and flour. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into sour cream mixture. Place 1/2 of zucchini in a baking dish.
Top with 1/2 sour cream mixture and 1/2 of the grated cheese.
Layer remaining zucchini, sour cream mixture and cheese.
Melt butter and stir in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: christmas amber rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt or tube pan. Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Blend well; then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Turn into pan.
Bake 55 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
While cake is cooling, prepare glaze.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows and coconut.
Mix sour cream (or yogurt) with sugar.
Stir into fruit mixture.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add tomato sauce, paste, basil and salt.
Spread half on cooked noodles.
Mix together cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley, eggs, salt and pepper.
Spread on top of meat mixture.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add grated cheeses.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients (except pecans) and form into ball or log. Roll in pecans and refrigerate.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven; drain.
Add other ingredients and cook several hours to give flavors time to blend.
Any other vegetables can be added.
This is even better the second day.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream oleo.
Add sugar and egg.
Beat until creamy.
Mix peeled and finely chopped apples together with nuts, flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Turn into buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for forty minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: *Granny Smith apples are recommended for this.

title: dump dessert
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: poppy cheese bread
directions: Slice bread at an angle (but not all the way through) from left to right, then right to left.
Stuff cuts with cheese.
Mix together remaining ingredients in a saucepan and simmer.
Cover bottom and sides of bread with foil.
Pour mixture over bread. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: minted zucchini
directions: Combine butter and oil in large skillet and heat until butter melts.
Add onion and saute over high heat about 1 minute.
Stir in zucchini.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is tender, about 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in mint and cook an additional 30 seconds.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Can leave out cocoa and make a chess pie.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, beating after each one.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes in a Bundt pan.

title: mexican salsa
directions: *If you use fresh tomatoes, clean as for canning.

title: peanut popcorn balls
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, add sugar, corn syrup, vinegar and peanut butter.
Cook until mixture reaches 260° on candy thermometer. Add vanilla.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Add all other ingredients (1/2 of Parmesan cheese, 1/4 cup).
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with other half of Parmesan cheese (1/4 cup).
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until it tests dry and top is slightly brown.
Do not undercook.

title: salmon puff
directions: Mix flaked fish and potatoes.
Add onion and celery, then add butter and egg yolks and fold in beaten egg whites last.
Place in buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° until brown.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry-pineapple mold
directions: Mix together; freeze in square pan.
Take out 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Place pieces on lettuce and allow to thaw a little.

title: butter nut chewies
directions: Preheat oven to
Grease
a
13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Melt Crisco.
Beat
eggs until light and foamy in a large bowl of electric
mixer.
Beat
in
sugar, vanilla and Crisco until creamy.
Combine
flour
with
baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix at low speed until blended.
Stir in nuts at low speed.
(Mixture will be stiff.) Spread evenly in prepared pan. Bake for
to 30 minutes or until top is light brown. Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: beef cream cheese spread
directions: Chop the chipped beef and mix with all the ingredients. Chill and serve with assorted crackers.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix nutmeg, cinnamon and Equal.
Mix with apples and add lemon juice, mixing well to coat apples.
Pour into prepared crust and bake in a preheated 425° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until crust is golden and mixture bubbly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form into a ball and roll in finely chopped nuts.

title: zucchini sweet relish
directions: Put zucchini and onion slices through food grinder.
Mix well with 5 tablespoons salt; let stand overnight.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain well in colander or sieve.
In a large kettle, mix vinegar, sugar, dry mustard, nutmeg, cornstarch, turmeric, celery seed and black pepper.
Cook until it starts to thicken.
Add ground vegetables and mix well.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Can it hot, sterilizing jars at once.

title: country sweet-sour cabbage
directions: In a large pan, add first 5 ingredients.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
When cabbage is tender, add brown sugar and vinegar.
If desired, salt and pepper.
Cook an additional 5 to 10 minutes to let the sugar/vinegar cook a bit.

title: hot creamed crab
directions: Beat cheese until smooth in small electric mixer.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, flour and pepper. Beat again until smooth.
Fold in crabmeat, almonds and salt to taste.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Place over heat (candle or other heating device).

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla together in a bowl.
Place milk in 4 cup glass measure.
Microwave milk on High setting for 3 1/2 to 4 minutes or until hot, but not boiling.
Gradually add hot milk to egg mixture, while continuing to beat.

title: nibblin fish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large plastic bag and shake to mix.
Serve.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Combine 2 cups buttermilk baking mix, 2/3 cup milk and 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese with a wooden spoon until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously 30 seconds. Drop dough by heaping tablespoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Combine 1/2 cup butter or margarine and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder. Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet. Serve warm. Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift together salt and flour.
Pour water into oil, then dump into dry ingredients.
Work in.
Form two balls; roll out.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients in a glass pie plate.
Sprinkle with a little more Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbly and golden.
Serve with cocktail breads or crackers.

title: franke's eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in small cubes.
Cook in salted water about 15 minutes.
Drain and mash; set aside.

title: chocolate-peppermint topping
directions: Combine whipped topping, syrup and extract in a bowl.
Blend well.
A particularly good topping for angel food cake.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in a greased loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Remove pan from oven and cover with cloth to cool.

title: never fail tupperware crust
directions: Combine ingredients in mixing bowl.
Put on lid and "burp". Shake hard for
60 seconds.
Divide dough in half and roll out thin on floured pastry sheet.
Makes 2 9-inch flaky crusts.
Easy and good.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut hot potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out potatoes, leaving skins intact for re-stuffing.
With wire whisk, beat potatoes with cottage cheese, milk and onion.
Spoon mixture back into skins.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley flakes.
You may also top with bacon bits, shredded cheese or other favorites. Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown in 350° oven.

title: christmas eve simple shepherd's pie
directions: In a large skillet, brown diced onion in small amount of fat. Add ground chuck.
Cook until done and crumbly.
Prepare mashed potatoes.
Cook frozen corn.
Slightly grease or spray nonstick cooking spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drain fat from meat. Spread crumbled meat in bottom of dish.
Spread cooked corn on top of meat.
Carefully spread mashed potatoes on top.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° to 350° until brown, about 1/2 hour.

title: mom's best krumkaker
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until thick.
Melt butter.
Cool.
Add slowly to egg and sugar mix, then add flour and cardamom.
Bake in krumkake iron on top of stove.
Remove with knife and roll in a cone shape on wooden cone.
Store in airtight box.
This makes about 60.

title: virginia spoon bread(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Scald milk in saucepan (do not boil); remove from heat.
Add cornmeal, whisking constantly until lump free, add butter; cool.
When sufficiently cool, add egg yolks.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate mixture overnight before rolling into ball.
Roll in additional cup of pecans.
Decorate with cherries or stuffed olives.

title: potatoes in cream sauce
directions: Blanch 4 diced potatoes by boiling for 7 minutes, ; drain and set aside.

In a small saucepan, combine remaining diced potato and water; bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for 10 minutes. With a hand mixer, blend potatoes until smooth; stir in butter buds, onion powder, bouillon granules and 1/2 c. milk until smooth.
Add more milk to reach a cream consistency.
Add pepper. Pour potato sauce over blanched potatoes.

title: quick easy appetizer
directions: Brown turkey in a skillet; drain any fat.
Cut Velveeta cheese in cubes and melt in skillet with turkey.
Serve in toast points (can be reheated).
Can put under broiler to re-warm or reheat in microwave.
Can serve with crackers to spread.

title: t.v. cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add flour, baking powder and soda.
Mix well, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Let set until cool.
If you use ice cream dipper, your cookie will be nice and round.
Bake on large cookie sheet.
These are also good with
half whole and half wheat. Makes about 36 cookies.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in milk and flavoring, add cherries and nuts.
Form into 2 inch rolls and roll in coconut to cover rolls.
Chill.
Cut in 1/4 inch slices.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 12 minutes.
Makes 60.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix in two round cake pans.
Break one cake into pieces and place in punch bowl.
Layer 1/2 of pudding mix on cake pieces.
Add layer of 1 can crushed pineapple (drained), 1 can pie filling and 1 container Cool Whip on top.
Then place next cake on top (do not break) and repeat with layering of pudding, crushed pineapple, pie filling and Cool Whip.
May add pecans.

title: fruit cookie pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat together butter and sugar until light and creamy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Gradually blend into butter mixture, just until moist.
Press dough evenly into 12-inch pizza pan.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or lightly brown.
Remove and cool.

title: soft sugar cookie puffs
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs; add cream and beat well.
Beat in the sugar, butter and almond extract.
Combine flour and baking powder; gradually add to sugar mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or until easy to handle.
On lightly floured surface, roll out dough to 1/4 inch thickness.
Make sure dough is thick enough so cookies will puff up.
Cut with cookie cutters dipped in flour. Place on greased baking sheets.
Sprinkle with colored sugars and bake or frost when cool.

title: orange pork steaks
directions: Look in the phone book under pizza.
Call, order your favorite kind and have it delivered (give name, address and phone number.) Wait for door bell to ring.
Open door, pay delivery man.
Grab some napkins and eat straight from box.
Refrigerate leftovers for breakfast.

title: garden glory
directions: Mix jello, mayo and cottage cheese.
Then add all other ingredients and mix well.
Chill 2 to 4 hours.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Mix juices and sugar in crock-pot.
Stud orange with cloves and add to liquid.
Add allspice and cinnamon sticks.
Simmer for 6 to 8 hours.
May add 1 cup rum, if desired.
Delicious at Christmas when your guests first arrive in from the cold.

title: green beans with cheese topping
directions: Combine green beans, onion soup mix and water; cover and cook over low heat 20 to 30 minutes or until beans are tender. Drain and spoon into a serving dish. Add butter, almonds and cheese; toss lightly. Sprinkle with paprika. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: party chicken
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spray with Pam or foil.
Put chicken breast in bottom of dish, top with 1 slice Swiss cheese on each breast.
Combine soup and wine; mix well.
Pour over chicken, add 1 cup of stuffing (or more if desired).
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored; add baking powder, salt and sugar and beat again.
Fold in flour and vanilla.
Line a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with waxed paper.
Bake at 400° for 13 minutes.
While cake is baking, place a towel, a little longer then the pan, on the table and sprinkle generously with powdered sugar.
When cake is done, immediately turn upside-down on the powdered sugar.
Remove waxed paper from bottom of pan.
Fold side of towel over cake and roll together to form a roll.
When cool, unroll cake and spread with your favorite jelly or preserves. Roll cake again and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Slice to serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook together sugar, water, crushed berries, cornstarch and lemon juice until thickened.
Add butter and cool while you spread softened cream cheese on baked crust.
Place whole berries on cheese.
Pour cooked mixture over all.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Combine cornbread mix with spinach.
Saute onion and salt in 3/4 stick butter.
Mix all together.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple and save syrup.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add cold water to syrup to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Add cold water and syrup to gelatin.
Chill until partly set.
Meanwhile, combine sugar and cranberries in bowl.
When jello is nearly set, add ground fruit, celery and nuts.
Place in mold, if desired.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 to 2 minutes after each. Sift flour, salt and soda. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beating after each addition.
Add milk; beat in well. Add extracts and vanilla. Beat well. Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, water and corn syrup in top of double boiler, beating with rotary or electric mixer until thoroughly mixed.
Place over rapidly boiling water.
Beat 7 minutes or until frosting stands in peaks.
Remove from boiling water.
Add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread.
Makes enough frosting for the top and sides of two 9-inch layers.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough until done, about 7 to 10 minutes.
Let cool, spread with mixture of cream cheese, sugar and a little vanilla. Decorate with whatever fruit you like.
You can also have Cool Whip on top, if desired.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Mix together orange marmalade, egg and shortening or oil.
Add to this mixture the flour, vanilla, soda and salt.
I also add some orange flavoring.
Stir in raisins and nut meats.

title: pace six layer dip
directions: Mash avocados in a bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream and mayonnaise in another bowl.

title: coconut candy
directions: To the coconut juice, add (if needed) enough sweet milk to fill a cup.
Boil sugar and juice for 6 minutes.
Add the coconut meat; boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Beat until creamy. Drop on buttered dish.
Let cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter until it forms a soft ball in water, then add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat with spoon until slightly stiff.
Pour into buttered pan.
Allow to cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: beefy cheese balls
directions: Shred beef in blender, save 1/2 cup.
With large spoon, stir in other ingredients.
Shape into 2 large balls.
Roll in remaining beef.
Refrigerate.
Serve at room temperature with your choice of crackers.

title: apple crumb cake(yield: 2 servings)
directions: Melt 1/3 cup
butter in a large skillet.
Pare, core and slice apples to 1/2-inch pieces.
Add apples to butter and cook, stirring, 8 minutes, until tender.
Stir in 3/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon lemon peel, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, mace and currants. Cook 15 minutes, stirring until thickened.
Cool.

title: easy chicken and noodles
directions: Boil chicken in 4 quarts of water with seasoning in water. Remove chicken and debone.
Cook noodles in chicken broth until done.
Add chicken and soups to the noodles.
Do not drain the noodles.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add water. Sprinkle onion over mixture.
Season chicken to taste; place, skin side up, on rice mixture.
Slightly dilute soup with milk; spread over top of chicken.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: children's play dough
directions: On medium heat, cook and stir until mixture dries and forms a mass, not sticky (watch, it goes fast).
Cool.
Keep in plastic bag.
Add coloring if desired.

title: elegant peanut pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs, corn syrup, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in peanuts and put in pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped cream.

title: pineapple pork chops
directions: In dish mix pepper, salt and flour.
Coat pork chops with flour mixture.
With meat mallet, pound chops on both sides.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Heat salad oil and sugar to boiling point; pour over the above and chill in refrigerator.
Keeps well for days if kept cold.

title: strawberry loaf
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Add cherry brandy.
Set aside.
Heat jam until melted.
(If preserves are used, force through sieve.)
Add strawberry extract and food coloring.
Set aside.
Cut pound cake horizontally into 3 even pieces.
Wash, dry and cap strawberries.
Reserve 6. Slice remaining berries.
Whip 1/2 of the cream and fold berries into it. Place bottom slice of cake on a serving plate.
Brush with cherry brandy syrup.
Spread half of berries-cream mixture on cake and top with a second slice of cake.
Add remaining slice of cake and brush with remaining syrup.
Beat the remaining cup of heavy cream with confectioners sugar until stiff.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Chill.
Grind cranberries.
Add sugar and other ingredients.
When Jell-O begins to thicken, combine mixtures.

title: milk punch
directions: Mix milk, sugar and bourbon and stir.
Add ice cubes and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve as an alternate to Bloody Marys.

title: homemade beef stock
directions: Wash beef and in deep pot cover with water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Strain, reserving beef and vegetables.
Stock may be used in place of oil to saute meat, vegetables, etc.
If stock is to be used as soup, blend vegetables and stock in blender for 30 seconds.
May be frozen.
Serving size 1 cup.

title: kielbasa and sauerkraut
directions: Place a layer of kraut in bottom of small roaster.
Slice some onions on top, then cut kielbasa in pieces and lay them on top of onions.
Keep making layers in this order with the minced garlic and bay leaf.
Top with bacon strips.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple-lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Whisk in sour cream until blended.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage until done.
Drain well.
Beat eggs.
Add eggs, milk, cheese and bread (which has been broken into pieces) with sausage and mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
If you use glass dish, bake at 325°.
Also sprinkle more cheese on top of mixture.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, Miracle Whip and chili powder.
Divide meat mixture, chips and cheese into half layer in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomato if desired.

title: no-knead parker house rolls
directions: Heat cup of water to boiling point and add sugar, salt and shortening. Cool to lukewarm. Pour the cup of lukewarm water into a bowl and add yeast. Let stand until dissolved and add the lukewarm water mixture, egg and flour. Beat until smooth. Place dough in greased bowl. Brush top with melted shortening. Cover and chill in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours. Roll out in a circle about 1/2-inch thick. Cut into rounds with cookie cutter. Crease heavily a dull edge of knife through center. Brush lightly with butter. Fold over in pocket shape and place on greased baking sheet 1-inch apart. Let rise until double in bulk. Bake in hot oven at 425° about 20 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press out rolls on pizza pan to form crust.
Sprinkle with seasoned pork sausage and uncooked hash browns.
Beat eggs and milk together; pour over pizza.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until eggs are done.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels and 1/2 cup sugar and butter.
Mix well and press into a long oblong dish.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1/4 cup sugar; spread on first layer.
Combine juice from pineapple and 2 tablespoons flour.
Cook until thickened.
Cool and mix with pineapples and place on top of second layer of salad.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Lay whole graham crackers over entire bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk and pudding mix.
When thick, add all of Cool Whip. Put 1/2 pudding mixture on layer of graham crackers.
Then put another layer of graham crackers, then rest of pudding mixture. Top with another layer of whole graham crackers.
Melt frosting in microwave.
Stir and spread over cake.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: old fashioned caramels
directions: Butter a 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Melt butter in heavy 3-quart saucepan. Add sugar and mix well. Stir in corn syrup.
Cook until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat. Stir in sweetened condensed milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 240°, soft ball.
It will take 20 to 30 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla. Pour into pan. Cool to room temperature. Slip spatula under corner and remove from pan.
Cut into small pieces. I wrap each piece with plastic wrap.

title: pilgrim pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco, sugar and salt very well. Add eggs and beat well. Add flour, milk and flavoring; beat well. Grease and flour TUBE pan. Pour mixture in pan; place in COLD oven and set temperature at 300°. Bake for 2 hours.

title: asparagus italiano
directions: Coat Prosciutto lightly with mixture of olive oil and thyme. Blanch asparagus until just tender (2 to 4 minutes).
Immerse blanched asparagus in ice water.
Drain.
Wrap each stalk with Prosciutto.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with lemon wedge.

title: mustard baked chicken
directions: Mix maple syrup, mustard, lemon juice and salt together.
Spoon over skinned chicken pieces.
Let stand at least 24 hours or overnight in sealed container.
Melt margarine and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
I use a glass pan.
Pour over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then turn oven up to 400° for another 20 to 30 minutes.
Every 15 minutes, baste chicken with sauce.
I serve the sauce to dip chicken in while eating.
Depending on chicken pieces, I even stretch sauce to cover 4 pieces of chicken.
Also, when using plain maple syrup, I add 1 to 2 tablespoons of honey.
Serve with rice pilaf.

title: french toast
directions: Preheat griddle to 350°.
Combine egg and milk.
Whip to desired consistency.
Add vanilla.
Add generous amount of ground cinnamon.
Dip bread in mix.
Lay to dry in single stacks for 1/2 hour (will absorb moisture).
Grease griddle with Pam or margarine.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: Mix well sugar, cornstarch and cold water.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Stir in egg yolks.
Slowly bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice, salt and margarine.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and milk.
Mix well.
Stir in pie mix and lemon juice.
Fold in with first mixture.
Pour into pie crusts.
Top with Cool Whip.
This is enough for two pies.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix these ingredients and chill.

title: crispy cheese rounds
directions: Mix all ingredients on low speed in a mixer.
When the mixture resembles wet sawdust, with clean hands, make cylinders about the diameter of a quarter.

Wrap the cylinders in wax paper. Place in the freezer. Leave in the freezer at least 1 1/2 hours or in freezer bags in freezer until ready to use within 2 months. Slice cylinders into rounds 1/8-inch to 1/4-inch wide (thinner rounds are more crisp).
Place 1-inch apart on a cookie sheet. Place a pecan half in the center of each.
Place in a preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned. After cooled, store in airtight container.

title: crunchy date rounds
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Stir in nuts and dates.
Drop from teaspoon into crushed flakes, rolling to coat well.
Place two inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Top with walnut halves. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool before removing from pan.
Makes three dozen.

title: beverly's lasagna
directions: Mix the ricotta cheese, egg, parmesan cheese and parsley. Layer in a 9 x 13 pan with the tomato sauce, lasagna noodles and Ricotta cheese mixture.
Top with mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in buttered casserole and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Coat a large, nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic; saute until tender.
Combine egg substitute and next 4 ingredients.
Stir in spinach.
Add mushroom mix, stirring well. Spoon in prebaked pastry shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Arrange cheese slices on top.
Bake 5 minutes until cheese melts.

title: roux
directions: Combine ingredients in heavy saucepan over medium-high heat for about 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and continue cooking and stirring until you get the color called for in the recipe.
Dark roux will take about 15 minutes.

title: potato chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine; add sugar gradually and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until light.
Add hot mashed potatoes and blend together.
Sift flour; measure and add salt, baking powder, chocolate and spices.
Sift again.
Add dry ingredients alternating with milk and vanilla.
Beat after each addition.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for layers, 1 hour for loaf.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 loaf pans and bake for 55 minutes at 350°.
Top should crack open; test with toothpick.
Glaze while hot.

title: navy bean soup
directions: If using dry beans, wash and sort.
In large kettle, cover the beans with 6 to 8 cups of hot water.
Bring to boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand for 1 hour.
Add another 8 cups cold water and ham pieces.
Bring to boil; simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in remaining ingredients; simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, until beans are tender.
Makes about 3 quarts soup.

title: copper pennies
directions: Pour oil in pan with chopped pepper and onions.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Add carrots and continue to simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons hot fat. Add and cook 5 to 10 minutes all ingredients except noodles or rice.
Heat thoroughly, then serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4.
Preparation time: 30 minutes.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine.
Press firmly into lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 250° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: shrimp and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large roasting pan, toss potatoes, peppers, salad oil and 1 teaspoon salt.
Roast vegetables in oven for 30 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking time. Meanwhile, slice green onions; peel and devein shrimp.
In bowl, toss green onions, shrimp and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Stir shrimp mixture into vegetable mixture; roast 10 minutes longer or until shrimp are opaque throughout and potatoes are fork-tender.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Fry beef and drain all fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Layer over tortillas and cheese a few times.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cream butter; add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs.
Beat nonfat dry milk, water and bananas until mixed well.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture, starting and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend well after each addition.
Fold in nuts.
Turn into pans and bake 50 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.

title: canadian margarita
directions: Pour into the blender (all in equal parts). Blend well. Enjoy!

title: friendship cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar in large bowl.
Beat well.
Add eggs, beat well.
Coarsely chop brandied fruit and stir into batter.
Add pecans and juice; mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: cherry divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water, and corn syrup in a 2-quart saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar is completely dissolved.
Stop stirring; continue cooking until 260° on candy thermometer or until a small drop hardens when dropped in cold water.
Meanwhile, beat egg whites in small bowl until stiff peaks form.
Continue beating egg whites while pouring the hot syrup in a fine stream into the whites, blending well.
Add vanilla.
Beat until mixture holds its shape and becomes slightly dull (this may take several minutes).
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Quickly drop mixture from tip of a buttered teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Allow to dry for 2 or 3 hours.
Then store in airtight container.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Spray casserole (1 1/2-quart dish) with Pam.
Layer with soup on bottom and end with asparagus on top.
Spread shredded cheese over top.
Dot with a little butter.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Set aside.
Cook rice, using 1 cup chicken broth.
Add cream of chicken and Cheddar cheese soup to rice.
Mix well.
Stir in chicken.
Place in casserole dish and bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: tater tot supreme
directions: Crumble ground beef loosely into rectangular baking dish. Sprinkle with onion flakes and peas; spread evenly with mushroom soup. Top with Tater Tots. Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until cooked through. Yield: 8 servings.

title: stew beef dinner
directions: In a large pot, cook beef until done.
Add onion (diced).
Cut potatoes in fourths.
Cut carrots and turnip in pieces and dump all in pot with stew beef.
Cook until all vegetables are about done.
Next add cabbage cut up over the top of recipe.
Cook until cabbage is tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mexican peanuts
directions: Saute
garlic
in
peanut
oil.
Stir
in the remaining ingredients.
Cook	for about 2 minutes in the open skillet at medium
heat.
As soon as they are cool enough to eat they may be served.
They
keep
well so they may be served later when they are cool.

title: easy mexican soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain fat.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: eggs for a crowd
directions: Blend milk, eggs and spices in blender.
Butter a 13 1/2 x 9 3/4-inch baking dish.
Layer with 8 slices of buttered bread. Cover with 3 cups grated cheese and 1/2 of egg mixture.
Repeat with second layer, using balance of ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Let rest before cutting.
Serves 12.

title: batter rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast. Stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm mixture, egg and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rise until double, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Punch down and shape into 2 dozen rolls.
Place on greased sheet and cover to let rise until double.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Add ingredients to tomato mix.
Bake mixture uncovered in oven at 350° for 6 hours or until desired thickness.
Pack in hot sterile jars.
Hot water bath 15 minutes.

title: chow mein
directions: Boil chicken until fully cooked; drain and break in small pieces.
Combine vegetables in skillet and fry until hot.
Add chicken, salt and pepper and fry for a few minutes.
Put noodles in a large pan with enough oil to coat the pan bottom.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and green onions. Heat through.
Add soy sauce, if desired.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream
sugar
and
oil together;
add eggs and vanilla. Then add
remaining
ingredients a little at a time; mix well. Spoon onto
greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well. Add all dry ingredients and mix well.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake approximately 1 hour or until done. Bake at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk. Add sour cream. Add 1/2 of Cool Whip. Layer mixture, vanilla wafers and bananas. Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: polvorones de canele(cinnamon cookies)
directions: First cream 1/2 cup plus 1 teaspoon of confectioners sugar and the margarine together.
Add the 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and work into a stiff dough. Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Mix together 1 cup of confectioners sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and roll the 1 inch balls into cinnamon mixture.
Place on greased sheets into oven set at 350° for about 15 - 20 minutes, until lightly browned. Cool well.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter.
Beat until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla, beating until light and fluffy. Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake. Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans on top.

title: coconut or chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa.
Beat egg yolks and combine with 1 cup of milk.
Mix together and cook over low heat or double boiler.
Then add remaining milk and butter.
Cook until very thick.
Add vanilla and stir.
If you are making coconut pies, add the coconut at this time and stir well.
Pour in 2 cooked pie shells and top with meringue.

title: sauteed chicken medallions
directions: Cut breasts into finger size pieces, whack flat, bread and saute in butter for about 4 minutes on each side.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine oleo and crumbs and pat into the bottom of a 13x9 -inch pan.
Beat eggs,
4 minutes.
Add powdered sugar, butter, and vanilla and beat 5 minutes more.
Spread over crumbs and chill. Spread pineapple and sliced bananas over former;
then topping, nuts, and cherries.
Refrigerate 6 hours, then serve.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Brown green pepper and mushrooms in melted butter.
Add almonds and brown slightly.
Add broth to heat.
Add rice.
Bake in casserole for approximately 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Whip together the whipped oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat into mixture.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix all together.
Grease and flour a tube cake pan.
Start in cold oven at 300° for 30 minutes, then at 325° for 50 minutes more (one hour and 20 minutes in all).

title: oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: Mix first three ingredients in saucepan and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir together, then drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Let cool in refrigerator.

title: harvest cake
directions: Let apples and sugar stand, mixed, for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients to same bowl.
Mix all ingredients until well blended. Bake in tube pan (ungreased) for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° or until toothpick, when inserted, comes out clean.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: el vundegas(meat ball soup)
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to boil before dropping in meatballs one at a time.
Shape last 4 ingredients into meatballs.
Simmer soup for 1 1/2 hours.

title: scalloped clams
directions: Combine onion, clams, parsley, salt and Tabasco.
Mix crumbs with butter.
Set aside 1/3 of crumb mix.
Combine remaining crumbs with clam mix.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Top with crumbs. Pour on heavy cream.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: Combine vegetables with salt and let stand 1 hour.
Place remaining ingredients in saucepan, bring to boil for 1 minute, cool and drain.
Add vinegar mixture to vegetables and stir gently.
Ladle into plastic freezer bags.
When ready to use, defrost and serve chilled.
Yields 1 1/2 to 2 quarts.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; shred cheese.
Drain macaroni and add stick of butter.
Mix in cheese.
Add can of milk and pepper.
Stir until blended.
Place in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Take out and stir and place in oven again for 10 minutes.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and flour together in large bowl.
Stir in butter and mix with hands until crumbly.
Remove 1 cup of mixture and save.
Place remaining crumbs in 8-inch pan; press firmly. Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on the box except use milk instead of water.
Bake.

title: salsa-cheese dip
directions: In microwave, cook chilies with onions and tomatoes until tender.
Slowly add cubes of Velveeta, microwaving and stirring each time until melted.
Dip should be thick.
Only add cheese until it reaches your desired consistency.

title: apple-nut cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour and dry ingredients. Add at intervals.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake at 350°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook to soft boil and pour over corn.

title: banana puff pie
directions: Combine all the ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Freeze. Take out of freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: cobbler(fruit)
directions: Put the stick of oleo in a deep baking dish.
Melt in oven at 350°.
Make a batter with sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted oleo.
Do not stir.
Empty fruit on top of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until done or for 1 hour.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix
sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar.
Cook over low heat for
minutes.
Add
butter and stir.
Pour sauce over beets. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes to absorb sweet/sour flavor of the sauce.

title: poached chicken breast
directions: Rinse breasts thoroughly under running cold water.
Place in a saucepan large enough to hold them in a single layer.
Add cold water to a depth of 1-inch above the breasts and any optional items.
Remove the breasts from the pan.
Set the pan over high heat and bring to a full boil.
Return breasts to pan, skin side down.
When water returns to boil, turn heat down low and simmer 17 minutes, checking to make sure bubbles continue to break the surface throughout the cooking.
Remove pan from heat and let breasts stand in the liquid for 30 minutes.
With a slotted spoon, remove breasts; when cool enough to handle, pull off skin and remove bones.
Serve immediately or refrigerate immediately. Serves 4.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients together and store in airtight container.
Use 2 teaspoons of tea to 1 cup of hot water or to taste.

title: raisin squares
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch nonstick or glass bakeware.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Wrap dried beef and bacon around
chicken breasts.
Place in casserole dish.
Combine sour cream and mushroom soup and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot mustard
directions: Mix together vinegar and mustard.
Let stand overnight.
Blend well the eggs, salt and sugar.
Cook over low to medium heat until mixture thickens.
Stir constantly.
Cool and then add mayonnaise. Mix well.
Makes 2 1/2 pints.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: For a brown crust when baking pecan or custard pies, place pie pan on iron skillet which is turned upside down.
Bake as usual.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Wash and cut lettuce, toss with onion. Scatter frozen peas over top of lettuce/onion - do not mix in. Seal with mayo and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; cover tightly and refrigerated overnight or 4 hours. Add bacon crumbles just before serving and toss well.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place 4 slices of bread in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle cooked sausage on top of bread, then cheese.
Place the last 4 slices of bread on top of cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour egg mixture over casserole.
Cover and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Grease dish.
Drain pineapple and spread in dish.
Mix sugar and flour and pour over pineapple.
Sprinkle cheese over next, then cracker crumbs.
Melt butter and drizzle over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: swiss cheese and onion soup
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Add garlic, onion, mustard and salt.
Saute until tender.
Add water.
Cover and simmer over low heat.
In a separate saucepan melt remaining 3 tablespoons butter.
Whisk in 3 tablespoons flour and cook, whisking over low heat 1 minute.
Slap a waffle (heat absorber) under the pan.
Add milk; cook whisking until uniform and thick, 5 to 8 minutes.
Add pepper, tamari, Tabasco and Worchestershire, horseradish, sherry, cheese and onions.
Cook over low heat 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, mayo, eggs, soup and mushrooms and a portion of cheese.
All ingredients should be evenly mixed.
Sprinkle the rest of the cheese on top and then add Ritz crackers, crumbled, to very top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes; uncover and cook for 10 more minutes.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Soak 1/2 pound garbanzos (chickpeas) overnight in salt water. Drain.
Add beans in soup pot with beef and ham bone and 2 quarts of water.
Cook slowly for 45 minutes.
Cut fat in liquid.
Add paprika and diced onion, fry slowly until the onion is light brown then add to the soup.
Add potatoes, saffron, salt and pepper. Cook until beans and potatoes are tender, then ladle into bowls with thin slices of Spanish sausage.

title: rhode island clam chowder(6 servings)
directions: Dice the cucumbers into 1/4-inch pieces and degorge (sprinkle with salt to draw out the excess water, then blot on paper towels).
Mix stock, tomato juice, yoghurt, garlic, salt and pepper.
Beat with a fork until smooth.
Drain cucumbers and add to the mixture.
Add the shrimp and chill.
Garnish with egg and mint or parsley just before serving.
This soup is smooth, cool and a delicate blushing pink, with the surprise flavor of cucumbers and shrimp.
Guests always want a copy of this recipe.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all in a blender and mix until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: currant muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and ginger.
Combine egg, milk and shortening; add to dry ingredients. Stir until all flour is moistened.
Fold in currants.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling cups 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Yields 18 muffins.

title: peanutty chocolate fudge
directions: In a heavy 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, evaporated milk and caramels.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until mixture comes to an overall boil.
Let boil for 5 minutes, stirring continuously. Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips and peanuts, until chips are melted.
Pour mixture into a buttered 8-inch square pan. Let cool completely.
Cut into 64 (1-inch) squares.

title: walnut apple crisp
directions: Toss apples in lemon juice and water in 2 quart baking dish. In large bowl combine flour, oats, sugar, nutmeg and salt. Mix thoroughly. Cut in butter in food processor to resemble coarse crumbs. Mix in walnuts. Crumble over apples to cover. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until top is light brown.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs longwise.
Place yolks in a small bowl.
Mash together the yolks, butter, cream and mustard until well blended.
Add olives and cayenne.
Fill whites with egg mixture.
Chill before serving.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and paprika. Put in buttered 13 x 9. Top with cheese and sprinkle paprika.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes or until shrimp turn pink and cheese is bubbly.

title: rocky road ice cream(based on 4-quart freezer)
directions: Combine milk and chocolate in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until chocolate is melted, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze as directed.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss together.
Add 1 cup mayonnaise and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Toss again.

title: french silk pie
directions: In small mixer bowl cream sugar and butter about 4 minutes or until fluffy.
Stir in cooled chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating on medium speed of electric mixer after each addition and scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Fill baked pastry shell and chill several hours or overnight.
Whip cream with remaining 1/4 cup powdered sugar and Amaretto until firm. Spread on top of pie.

title: brisket
directions: Place brisket in roaster pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover pan with foil to make airtight for 24 hours or overnight.
Bake 4 hours at 250°.
Slice thinly and bake 1 hour more.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion until soft.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: super-easy orange chocolate chip ice cream mold
directions: Place a 3-cup mold in refrigerator to chill.
Stir cream, sugar and orange juice in a medium-size bowl until sugar dissolves. Place in freezer 1 1/2 hours or until partially frozen (mixture must be thick so chips won't sink).
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into chilled mold, cover and freeze until hard, several hours or overnight.

title: pat in pan pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well with fork.
Pat in pie plate.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes or use for uncooked pie crust.

title: soft breadsticks
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Add sugar, salt and oil. Stir until dissolved. Add 2 cups flour. Beat until smooth. Add enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured surface. Knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size, about 1 hour. Punch down and divide into 12 portions. Roll each portion into a 10 x 1/2-inch rope. Place 1-inch apart on a greased baking sheet, sprinkled with cornmeal. Let rise, uncovered, until doubled, about 40 to 60 minutes. Beat egg white and water. Brush over breadsticks. Sprinkle with coarse salt. Place baking sheet on middle rack of oven. Place a large shallow pan filled with boiling water on lowest rack. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Brush again with egg white. Bake 5 minutes longer or until golden brown. Yield: 1 dozen.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Crush Ramen noodles (do not cook). Mix all.

title: apple cider
directions: This recipe may be halved.
Place all ingredients in container and simmer for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Spices may be tied in a bag, if desired.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut celery and put in large pan.
Flour and brown meat that has been cut in bite size.
Drain on paper towel, then add to celery, soy sauce and brown sauce.
Cut onions and brown them. Add to rest.
Cook until meat is tender, about an hour or so.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into patties (golf ball size).
Fry in vegetable oil until golden brown on both sides.
If you wish, shape into loaf and bake at 370° for 45 minutes in greased loaf pan.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Put the cooked and drained vegetables in a greased casserole. Add the soups.
Put Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until it bubbles.
Bake with lid on.

title: skillet fried peach pies
directions: Combine peaches and sugar. Add water to cover. Cook down until tender. Mash peaches with potato masher and let cool. Cut pastry dough about 5 x 8-inches. Place 1/4 cup peaches in each crust. Fold over and stick edges of crust together. You may have to dampen edges to get them to stick good. Fry until brown in a well-greased skillet.

title: portuguese rice pudding
directions: Bring milk and water in saucepan to a boil (watch carefully). Turn to low; add rice.
Cover 20 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Pour sugar; mix quickly (will be soft).
Mix eggs separately, then mix together with rice.
Again mix quickly.
Let set in serving dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: parmesan party rounds
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in green onion. Spread a thin layer of mixture on each slice of bread.
Place on a baking sheet.
Broil about 4 inches from heat until bread is lightly toasted.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
Approximately 5 1/2 dozen.

title: low calorie salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle dry jello over top.
Fold in drained fruits.
For variations, use other jello.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill overnight.

title: peach cookies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour and baking powder.
Make 1-inch balls (do not press) and bake on greased and floured cookie sheets for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, hollow out cookies and when cool, fill with apricot filling.
Mix 1/2 pint white vermouth and 6 drops red food color.
Roll cookies in vermouth, then white sugar and add peach leaves.
Yield:
5 dozen cookies (2 1/2 dozen peaches).

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix together potatoes, salt and pepper.
Add egg and enough flour to thicken batter.
Heat oil in skillet.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls into skillet.
Cook until evenly browned on both sides.

title: night before egg casserole
directions: Use cooking spray to coat 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Pour croutons in pan to cover bottom.
Cover with 1/2 cheese and meat. Combine eggs, milk, dried mustard, soup and salt and pepper.
Pour liquid mixture over contents of pan.
Spread rest of cheese over liquid.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Remove plastic wrap or foil and bake for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add melted margarine.
Add beaten eggs and salt, stir well.
Add flour, stirring well again, finishing with nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 pan, bake 350 for 40 minutes.
Cool, cut into squares.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: french bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Add 4 cups flour and mix very well.
Add remaining flour, 1 cup at a time and knead in.
Place in greased bowl and punch down every 10 minutes for 1 hour.
Divide into 2 balls and let set for 10 minutes.
Roll into rectangle, then roll up into 2 long loaves. Place on greased cookie sheet and clip top every 2-inches.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and noodles supreme
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, prepare noodles according to package directions.
Add broccoli for last 5 minutes of cooking time. Drain.
In saucepan, add soup, sour cream, Parmesan cheese, pepper, noodles and broccoli.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Makes 5 servings.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: chicken rotel spaghetti
directions: Place chicken in water to cover and simmer until tender; debone and cut into bite-size pieces.
In same broth, cook spaghetti (do not drain).
In skillet, saut onion and green pepper in butter.
Add flour and blend well.
Add mushrooms and tomatoes.
Simmer about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.	Add Ro-Tel mixture to cooked spaghetti.
Stir in Velveeta cheese.
Add chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients together and mix well.
Add cornbread mix last and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Combine
the lettuce, celery, onion, peas, water chestnuts and broccoli.	Cover
with
1	cup
mayonnaise and 1 cup salad dressing
and
the	sugar.	Mix
with mayonnaise.
Use 2 cups mayonnaise	or
salad dressing, mix sugar in and salt and pepper to	taste.	Layer
lettuce on bottom of dish; spread to edge of dish.
Add	the
chopped tomato over mayonnaise, then add the crumbled
bacon.
Add
the	shredded
cheese over the bacon. Cover; let set for 24 hours.
Do not mix to serve.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Blend sugar, cream cheese and salt.
Fold in whipped topping.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass dish.
Cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving time.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce. Garnish with fresh strawberries if desired.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Chill peas, celery, onions, rice and shrimp. Combine and blend well all remaining ingredients. Pour over chilled mixture. Toss lightly and let stand in the refrigerator for several hours (preferably overnight).

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Thoroughly combine eggs, sugar, margarine, lemon juice and vanilla; stir in coconut.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edges comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: chocolate lover's chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two (9-inch) round cake pans.
Line bottom of pans with wax paper.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add beaten eggs, butter and milk. Mix well.
Heat until hot on top of stove.
Pour into deep dish pie shell. Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown. Top with meringue and brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and divide into 2 casseroles. Bake at
350° for 40 minutes.

title: caramel pecan cheese cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour into graham cracker crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn oven off and open door.
Cool pie in oven to room temperature.
Remove from pan and refrigerate, if desired.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Lightly brown onion and celery in butter.
Add next 4 ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.
Put into buttered casserole.
Top with layer of nuts and noodles.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Beat milk, water, drippings and bouillon cubes until all are dissolved.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix well.
Press out on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Cut into shapes (of dog bones).
Bake at 300° for one hour, then turn off heat and leave in oven until they harden.

title: ed's brunswick stew
directions: Boil meat together until tender.
Cool and remove meat from bones.
Save meat broth.
Grind meat with onions using coarse blade on food chopper.
Add corn, tomatoes, butter and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer mixture 3 to 4 hours.
Gradually add meat stock after having skimmed off fat.
Serves 30 people.
This freezes well.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on box.
Now mix all the other ingredients together with pudding and chill in a mold or dish.

title: pork tenderloin with red wine
directions: Boil 1/2 cup of water in a heavy pot; add bouillon cube.
Sear pork in hot butter, turning with tongs until brown.
Lower heat; add bouillon liquid, herbs, vegetables and a little wine.
Cook for 1 hour; turn.
Add more wine.
Cook another hour; remove meat and keep warm.
Drain vegetables from cooking liquid and mash. Return all to the pot.
Mix cornstarch with cold water.
Add to pot to thicken sauce, stirring
all the while. Serve sauce with the meat.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Halve peppers lengthwise.
Remove stems, seeds and membranes. Add salt to enough boiling water to cover peppers.
Boil 5 minutes; drain.

title: chicken veggie alfredo
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in oil. Transfer to a slow cooker. In a bowl, combine the Alfredo sauce, corn, peas, mushrooms, onion, water, garlic salt and pepper. Pour over chicken. Cover and cook on low for 6-8 hrs. Serve over linguine. Yield 4 servings.

title: microwave chip dip
directions: Melt cheese in microwave.
Add hamburger and seasoning.
Mix together.

title: orange loaf cake
directions: Cut orange.
Squeeze over 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Grind the orange peel and raisins twice.
Cream remaining 1 1/2 cups sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, then milk, mixed with the soda, orange/raisins and flour.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Spoon sugar/juice over hot cake.

title: sweet and sour beef stew
directions: Brown meat cubes in hot oil.
Add the next 6 ingredients plus 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cover and cook over low heat until meat is tender (approximately 2 hours).

title: mom's bean soup
directions: Place beans in a 4-quart Dutch oven with 6 to 8 cups water. Heat to boiling and let simmer for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain.
Add 2 quarts water, ham, onion, garlic, parsley, salt, basil, pepper, oregano and bay leaf. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in jars.
Bring mixture to boil.
Pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: fried vidalia onion rings
directions: Follow directions for waffles on the Bisquick package.
Coat onion rings with batter, several at a time.
Drop into hot oil (about 375°) and cook 2 to 3 minutes, turning, if necessary, to brown evenly.
Drain on paper towels and salt to taste while still hot.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: chicken swiss
directions: Top chicken with cheese.
Mix vermouth with soup.
Spread over chicken.
Top chicken with stuffing mix.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swiss fondue
directions: Cut the bread in bite size pieces, taking care that each piece has a portion of crust.
Heat the garlic with the wine in the chafing dish pan until air bubbles appear; remove the garlic.
Mix the cheese with flour and salt.
Add to wine in three installments, stirring with a wooden spoon until cheese has melted.
Stir until mixture bubbles.
Have each guest spear his piece of bread on a fondue fork, dip it into the fondue and stir until bread is coated.
If the fondue becomes too thick, stir in warm wine.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and beat on high with mixer for 15 minutes until consistency of marshmallow cream.
Grease cookie sheets and drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add cream cheese to jello mixture.
Add all other ingredients except Seven-Up.
Mix well. Stir in Seven-Up.
Chill in refrigerator.
Stir.

title: one meal brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place beef brisket in large baking dish or roaster.
Mix next 7 ingredients and pour over brisket.
Place in oven and bake for 2 hours.
Add vegetable to pan and continue baking for 2 additional hours or until done.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Submerge tea bags in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Dissolve jello in tea; cool in ice until it starts to gel.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate until congealed.

title: low calorie frosting
directions: Place water, lemon juice and vanilla in bowl.
Sprinkle in dry milk.
Turn beater to high speed and whip for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Spread	crescent
rolls out on cookie sheet. Bake until brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in water until tender, about 45 minutes. When cool enough, peel potatoes and mash.
Add butter, sugar, spices, eggs and milk in large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until crust is brown.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: cool mandarin salad
directions: Mix together jello, tapioca pudding and water and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool. Add Cool Whip, oranges and pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: smoothie mango shake
directions: Combine mangos, ice, honey and milk in blender or food processor.
Puree until thick consistency.
Serve in glasses with a mint garnish.
Serves 4.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add sour cream and bananas. Stir in dry ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan and let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until it tests done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy and sugar is dissolved.
Add egg yolks, beating well.
Combine buttermilk and soda, stirring until soda dissolves.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Add 1 1/2 cups of chopped walnuts and coconut, stirring well.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting; sprinkle top with chopped walnuts.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put cheese, half and half and oleo in a saucepan and melt into a smooth sauce, stirring constantly.
Grate the potatoes and stir in sauce, mixing thoroughly.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch casserole, packing firmly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spread sour cream on top and spread onions evenly over the top. Fry and crumble bacon on top of the green onions.
Put back in the oven and bake 5 minutes longer or more.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Add margarine.
Mix sugar, salt and vanilla with beaten eggs.
Add broken pieces of bread to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Add milk and raisins and mix well.
