Pour into large baking pan.
Set in pan of water.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Makes 35 to 40 servings.

title: bean and bacon sandwich
directions: Mix beans and relish and put filling on bread slices.
Top with bacon (and cheese, if desired).
Heat in a 400° oven or microwave until hot and cheese melts.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cube round steak; add salt, paprika, pepper and onion.
Brown in melted butter; add bay leaf, Worcestershire sauce and soup. Simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Add sour cream just before serving.
Don't let boil after adding sour cream.

title: out of the world pie
directions: Cook pie filling, sugar, pineapple, cornstarch and coloring until thick.
Remove from heat and add dry jello.
Allow to cool. Add bananas and pecans.
Pour into pie shell and top with whipped topping.

title: sweet gherkin pickles(gherkins, immature cucumbers, are often made into sweet pickles.)
directions: First Day:
In the morning, wash cucumbers thoroughly.
Scrub with vegetable brush.
Drain cucumbers and place in large container.
Cover with boiling water.
That afternoon, 6 to 8 hours later, drain and cover with fresh boiling water.

title: sausage nacho dip
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Melt cheese; mix all ingredients together.
Keep hot for dipping.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry fresh, firm mushrooms.
Dip in beaten egg and dredge in flour.
Preheat oil to 375° on deep-fat thermometer or until a 1-inch cube of bread browns in 60 seconds.
Fry mushroom until brown, then drain on paper towels.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: festive punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid and orange juice by directions on package. Chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, mix all ingredients together.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind together the first 3 ingredients and add the salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain and add vinegar and sugar.
Boil 15 minutes. Cool and add mayonnaise and mustard.
Mix and seal.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together and heat in a microwave.
Stir as cream cheese melts.
Serve with bread sticks.

title: rum cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts evenly in bottom of tube pan, greased and floured.
Combine cake mix, eggs, water, oil and rum in large mixing bowl.
Blend and mix for 4 minutes on medium speed.
Pour over pecans.
Bake for about 1 hour at 325° or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing.
Glaze with Rum Glaze while cake is still warm.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Put salt over top; drain and rinse.
Heat vinegar, sugar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed until sugar dissolves.
Add pickles and onions.
Heat.
Put in canning jars.
Process in a water bath for 5 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Roll on floured board 1/4-inch thick and bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: acorn squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt margarine in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Parboil squash in a small amount of water.
Scoop pulp out. Place in a bowl; add remaining ingredients, except cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Put all the ingredients into baking dish in the order listed and squeeze margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: baked beans deluxe
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on absorbent paper.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Combine all ingredients, except bacon, in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; mix well.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Stir together cornstarch, broth and soy sauce.
Set aside.
In skillet over medium heat in 2 tablespoons hot oil, stir-fry chicken until no longer pink.
Remove and set aside.
In skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot oil, stir-fry veggies, garlic and ginger until tender-crisp.
Stir in broth mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Return chicken to skillet.
Heat through.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: yo-yo's
directions: Mix flour, milk, and salt.
Stirring until smooth; then cook until smooth, stirring constantly. Set aside and cool.

title: crunchy nut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Mix and sift together flour, soda and salt.
Stir into first mixture.
Add chopped nuts.
Shape 1 level tablespoon of dough into balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten with fork that has been dipped in cold water.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well; make into balls.
Melt the paraffin and chocolate chips in pan, then drop balls into chocolate mixture.

title: potato casserole(hand me downs)
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend flour, butter and powdered sugar; press in pie pan with fingers.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until slightly brown.

title: wild rice salad with basil and tomatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Serve on lettuce leaves with tomato wedge garnish.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Lightly brown hamburger; add onions and cook until onions are soft.
Add the 2 cans of tomatoes and cook for 10 minutes, medium heat.
Add the frozen corn and peas and cook 10 minutes.
Add the cooked rice.
Season to taste and cook until heated through.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring to cheese and beat in eggs.
Add flour and salt to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: raspberry pie or strawberry
directions: Boil sugar, cornstarch and water until thickened and clear; add jello and few drops food coloring.
Let cool; add berries and pour into baked crust.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Toss first 5 ingredients together, add tortilla chips and toss. Slice and add avocado.
Brown meat, add beans and salt; simmer for 10 minutes.
Mix with cold salad, decorate with tortilla chips, avocado and tomatoes slices.

title: heath bars
directions: Break crackers in half, then layer them out on aluminum foil-lined cookie sheet.
Boil together for 3 minutes (medium-low heat) the margarine, sugar and butter.
Pour over crackers, then cover with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and cut, then layer on aluminum foil and put in a tin to store.

title: 2-coconut pies
directions: Pour melted margarine over sugar. Add beaten eggs, milk, coconut and vanilla. Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° on lowest shelf for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: fat-free sweetened condensed milk substitute
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Let cool.
Add nonfat dry milk and beat or put into blender until smooth. This equals a 14 ounce can of milk.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with nonstick spray.
Tear 4 slices of bread into small pieces.	Cover bottom of pan with bread pieces.	Brown sausage and mix with eggs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls in bottom and up sides of a greased pizza pan. Smooth seams.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Soften cream cheese; mix with mayonnaise and dry dressing mix.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with cheese and vegetables. Cover; refrigerate until served.
Cut into slices or squares.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend flour and shortening well.
Add sugar, baking soda, eggs and mashed bananas.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased, lightly floured loaf pan at 350° to 375° for one hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and combine with macaroni.
Add 1 boiled egg (chopped).
Chill before serving.

title: preservation of newspaper clippings
directions: Mix together.
Let stand 24 hours.
Put clippings in solution. Let it soak for 2 hours.
This will neutralize acids in paper. This keeps clippings from turning yellow.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 200 cookies.

title: sobol's bar-b-q sauce
directions: Assemble and mix the ingredients.

title: buttermilk milk pie
directions: Beat the sugar, flour, butter and eggs real good.
Add the buttermilk and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Cook at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: easy supper dish
directions: Brown meat in heavy skillet.
Add salt when done.
Add Spanish rice and simmer about 15 minutes, covered.

title: baked perch fillets
directions: Sprinkle fish with onion salt and pepper.
Place in baking dish.
Combine Tabasco sauce and buttermilk.
Pour over fish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until fish flakes.
Serves 2.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box and cool. Crumble into small pieces.
Prepare pudding according to directions on package.

title: mock "bisquick" mix
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, milk and salt.
Blend in Crisco thoroughly.
Store and use like Bisquick.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add sugar. Beat until stiff. Add salt and vanilla. Mix well; add pecans and chocolate bits and drop by teaspoonful on ungreased foiled cookie sheets (2). Heat oven to 350°. Put in and turn off immediately and take out in morning. Makes 4 dozen.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: * You may wish to use additional confectioners sugar and lemon juice for an even yummier taste!

title: taco casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook ground beef until brown; drain.
Stir in beans, tomato sauce, taco sauce, chili powder and garlic powder.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Place tortilla chips in ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Top with beef mixture. Spread with sour cream.
Sprinkle with onions, tomato and cheese. Bake, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.
Arrange additional chips around edge of casserole; serve with shredded lettuce, chili peppers and taco sauce if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute 1/2 cup onion and 1/2 cup chopped green pepper in butter.
Add cream of chicken soup and onion soup.
Mix together with cooked rice.
Bake in a large dish; top with cheese of your choice.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: oven baked eggs
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine, then stir in flour and salt until blended.
Slowly add Sprite and milk, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Add cheese and stir until it is melted into the mixture.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Break eggs into the sauce.
Bake at 350 degrees until eggs become firm. Serves 6.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Cut apples after coring and paring, if skins are tough, into fairly large pieces.
Some apples, like Cortlands, do not darken as quickly when cut for a salad.
Add lemon juice, chopped celery and walnuts; toss to mix.
Chill.
Mix with mayonnaise for serving on a bed of lettuce.
Chopped candied ginger also may be added to the salad.

title: quick and easy peach pie
directions: Combine everything, except fruit.
Sprinkle over fruit in deep pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fancy chicken salad
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Serve in small pastry tart shells or crackers, as sandwich spread or on lettuce leaf.
This can be made with canned tuna in spring water, rather than chicken.

title: pecan buttermilk pralines
directions: Mix sugar, soda and milk in heavy saucepan and cook over medium heat
to
soft
ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat and add vanilla and pecans.
Begin beating immediately.
Beat until candy begins
to
thicken.
Drop
by teaspoon on waxed paper or greased baking sheet.
Cool.
Yields 30 small patties.

title: bite-sized chili rellenos
directions: In a bowl, whisk together the flour and salt; add the beer and whisk until batter is smooth.
Let the batter stand, covered, at room temperature for at least 1 hour and up to 3 hours.
Cut chilies into 3/4-inch strips; cut cheese into 3/4 x 1/2 x 1/2-inch pieces.
Wrap a strip of chili around each piece of cheese; secure the chili and cheese with a toothpick and chill the cheese morsels on a plate for 1 hour.
In a deep saucepan or wok, heat approximately 1 cup oil until it is hot but not smoking.
Stir the batter and coat the cheese morsels in batter, allowing any excess to drip off.
Fry them in the oil, turning frequently, for 15 seconds or until they are golden and crisp.
Transfer the chilies to paper towels to drain and discard the toothpicks.
Makes about 20 hors d'oeuvres.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix thoroughly. Add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy.

Flavor with love and kindly service. Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith. After pouring all this into your daily life, bake well with the heat of human kindness. Serve with a smile anytime and it will satisfy the hunger of starved souls. You never test the resources of God until you attempt the impossible.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Follow directions on package for cooking macaroni, then drain and wash with cold water.

title: peanut butter mousse pie
directions: Whip cream cheese at low speed until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter at medium speed.
Slowly beat in milk; fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Pour half of filling into each shell.
Sprinkle each pie with peanuts.
Freeze until firm, and then cut into wedges.
If stored for any length of time in freezer, wrap pie before freezing to exclude air.

title: chocolate ooey-gooey butter cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: mom's ranch stew
directions: Brown meat (drain fat), onion (chopped fine) and pepper.
Add other ingredients and simmer in a large pot at least 20 minutes. Serve with cornbread, rolls or crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Mix together mayonnaise, soup and onion.
Add broccoli.
Beat eggs well and add to broccoli mixture.
Pour into 9 or 10-inch casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Add a little extra grated cheese scattered on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mary's peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, powdered sugar, peanut butter and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust and freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion, chilies and garlic in oil until soft.
Add tomatoes, bouillon, chicken broth, water, tomato juice, cumin, chili powder, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and steak sauce. Bring soup to boil; lower heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Put tortilla strips in bottom of bowl.
Spoon on soup.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour or more.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Beat margarine and shortening until light and creamy.
Add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add flour and mix well, adding milk a little at a time.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour mixture into three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Frost with:

title: date-nut cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix the flour and soda and add to creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix well and marinate meat for 2 hours.
Baste often.
Very good for "Shish Kabobs".

title: rice pudding
directions: In a heavy saucepan, bring the milk just to the boil. Stir in the rice and the raisins or fruit. Cook covered for 30 or 40 minutes or until most of the milk is absorbed, stirring occasionally.

You may wish to leave the lid off during the last 8 to 10 minutes. Remove pan from heat; add sugar and vanilla. Spoon into dessert cups and sprinkle with nutmeg. Serve warm or chilled. Makes 6 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Watch closely so as not to brown too much.
Cool.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix the flour with the sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in a 350° oven until a knife inserted will come out clean, about 45 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Drain off any grease.
Place hamburger in soup kettle.
Add water.
Bring to a boil.
Boil on low heat for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bring back to boil on medium heat.
Cook for 30 minutes on low.

title: dirty rice dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours or more.

title: green split-pea soup
directions: Fry bacon in 5-quart pan.
Remove bacon, drain and save 1 1/2 tablespoons grease.
Add onion, carrots and celery.
Cook over medium heat 3 minutes.
Add peas, ham hock, water, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, lower heat and simmer covered 1 1/2 hours.
Remove hock, cut off meat and return to soup.
Crumble bacon.
Garnish with crumbled bacon and toasted croutons.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Pour into greased long cookie sheet pan, 11 x 17-inch.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: noodle cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain well and add mushroom soup, evaporated milk and mushrooms.
Spread half of noodle mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with layer of shredded cheese.
Spread on remaining noodles.
Sprinkle again with shredded cheese and top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until bubbly and slightly browned.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix by directions on box.
Pour half of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes; remove from oven. While cake is baking, in saucepan, combine butter, caramels and milk.
When sauce is melted and smooth, add pecans.
Spread sauce filling over hot cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Add remaining cake batter and spread over top of filling.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely and cut in squares.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour half the batter in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Melt caramels with milk and butter over low heat, stirring constantly. Pour over cake. Sprinkle with 1 cup nuts and chocolate chips. Pour remaining batter over filling. Sprinkle with remaining nuts. Bake 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter and remove from heat. Stir in brown sugar and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time stirring until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.

title: quick and easy low-fat cobbler
directions: Place pie filling in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Pour dry cake mix over pie filling.
Melt margarine; pour over cake mix. Sprinkle on pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with low-fat ice cream.

title: easy cream cheese clouds
directions: Mix
cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed on electric
mixer.
Gradually
add
heavy cream; mix well.
Whip until thickened.
Using the
back
of
a
spoon, shape into 10 (3 1/2-inch) shells.
Place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet. Freeze 2 hours or	overnight.
When
ready to serve, fill with cherry pie filling. Sprinkle chopped nuts on top, if desired.

title: cereal croutons
directions: Mix seasoned salt, celery salt and garlic powder.
Heat oven to 250°.
Put oil in shallow baking pan; tilt to coat pan.
Add cereal and toss.
Sprinkle with salt mixture and toss.
Bake 15 minutes and stir well.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Cool on paper towels.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine meatball ingredients.
Shape meat mixture into 1-inch balls.
Bake in a shallow baking dish at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain excess grease from meatballs.
Mix chili sauce and jelly in a microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave until jelly melts. Pour over meatballs.
Serve in a crock-pot or chafing dish.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Tie all spices together in cheesecloth.
Chop vegetables fine. In a large bowl, combine vegetables, cover with salt and let stand overnight, covered with cheesecloth.
In morning, drain vegetables; press through cheesecloth, squeezing out as much liquid as possible.

title: honey-mustard chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Mix the honey and mustard together. Grease the bottom of your pan or casserole dish.
Put chicken in the pan.
Brush sauce on both sides and put it in the oven at 350°.
Bake for 2 hours until golden brown.

title: pierogi(stuffed tiny pies)
directions: Do not add milk or seasoning when you mash the potatoes.
Cook onion in butter or margarine until tender.
Combine with potatoes, dill, salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in cottage cheese.
Makes 2 cups.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and place in casserole dish. Spread soup over top. Bake at 350° until soup bubbles. Take from oven and stir. Place onion rings on top. Bake until brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in 8-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs with a fork. Mix flour and sugar until well blended and add to eggs.
Add remainder of ingredients and pour into dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Cut frozen cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange cookie slices slightly overlapping on 13-inch pizza pan.
Press edges to seal.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool slightly.
Loosen cookie from pan, then allow to finish cooling on pan.
Blend cream cheese and sugar well.
Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit on cream cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Mix evaporated milk and meat.
Divide into 5 patties.
On waxed paper, pat each to 6-inch circle.
Put 1/4 cup of stuffing into center of each.
Fold meat over and seal.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and Mandarin oranges.
Add dry jello to cottage cheese and stir.
Add fruit and Cool Whip.

title: pea pods and chicken salad oriental
directions: *Pea pods should be trimmed and blanched (boil in water 1 minute, drain and rinse with cold water).

title: rice noodle casserole
directions: Melt butter, crumble noodles into it and brown for a few minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350 for about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: krispy cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Shape into balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in flour. Bake at 350° until done.

title: spinach bars
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon into a pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool slightly before cutting.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal. Set aside. Mix together brown sugar, Wesson oil, flour, salt, white sugar, whole eggs and soda. Mix all together and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma barre's icebox cake
directions: Beat whipping cream until thick and frothy.
Add chocolate syrup for flavor and color.
Spread chocolate cream mixture between graham crackers, making a stack and alternating mixture between graham crackers.
Leave enough chocolate cream mixture to spread over entire stack.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice on an angle to serve the next day.
Be creative; add a decorative topping, such as chocolate sprinkles, etc.
Be sure to spread enough chocolate cream mixture so the graham crackers do not dry out.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add vanilla and water. Add flour and mix well.
Add nuts and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cut up beef.
Mix soup and milk.
Add cheese, onion and beef. Stir in macaroni.
Store, covered, in 1 1/2-quart casserole 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
If necessary, add more milk before baking.

title: school bean chowder
directions: Cook beans in 3 quarts of water or more, depending on dryness of beans.
When beans are nearly done, add 1/2 teaspoon chili powder and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
While beans are cooking, combine meat, onions and garlic.
Brown in skillet on top of stove or 350° in oven, stirring frequently.
Add puree, chili powder, salt and bread crumbs.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine meat mixture and beans. May have to add more water for desired seasoning and consistency. Makes 3 quarts.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Brown hamburger with onion and drain. Add other ingredients along with macaroni.
Put in pan. Spread cheese on top, then add pepperoni.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken breasts and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice evenly into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients, except chicken and Parmesan cheese.
Pour 1/3 of the mixture over rice.
Arrange chicken breasts over soup mixture; cover with remaining soup mixture.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, buttermilk, flour, baking powder, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll out and cut out.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Mix and boil the above ingredients. Pack cucumbers in jars with dill, garlic, and hot pepper. Pour hot solution over and let stand 10 minutes, then pour solution off, in jug and save for the next batch. Pour fresh solution in each jar and seal, use hot lids and rings.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and vinegar.
Cook for 20 minutes. Dip each peach in boiling water.
Remove skin by rubbing with a cloth.
Stick 2 cloves into each peach.
Cook in the syrup until tender.
Do not cook too many at one time.
Place cooked peaches in preheated glass jars. Boil remaining syrup for 10 minutes. Pour over peaches.
Seal jars.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and butter together thoroughly. Add salt and egg; beat again.
(Add soda to sour cream.)
Add to above ingredients.
Beat again and fold in flour. Chill before rolling out for cookies. The dough is rich and soft.
I have better luck if I freeze the dough, then work with small amounts at a time.
You may need to add extra flour when rolling out to cut. These are very good.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs; add to pumpkin, then all liquids.
Mix dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: easy portuguese soup
directions: Fry Portuguese sausage in a large pot until brown.
Add onion and garlic; fry a little.
Add tomato sauce plus 1 can of water. Then add kidney beans plus 1 can water.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1/2 cup macaroni, carrots and potatoes.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Cook for 1/2 hour until noodles, carrots and potatoes are cooked.
If gravy is too thick, add more water.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in greased/floured tube or Bundt pan.
Cake will crack slightly on top.
Cool in pan 1 hour before removing.
Use cream cheese frosting or serve plain.

title: debbie's salad
directions: Put spinach in bowl.
Press down and season with salt and pepper.
Add bacon and chopped eggs.
Break lettuce and put on top.
Season again and layer next with peas and onions, then cheese.
Cover completely with mayonnaise.
Cover bowl tightly and put in refrigerator overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots with salt until tender; cool and drain.
Cook sugar, soup, vinegar and seasonings until thick and mustard dissolves.
In a dish layer carrots, green pepper and onion.
Pour mixture over, then another layer and more mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Stir in other ingredients. Bake in greased loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread graham cracker crumbs in pan.
Sprinkle on coconut.
Pour condensed milk over coconut. Sprinkle on both kinds of chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: earthcake dessert
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cover bottom of cake pan with coconut.
Cover coconut with chopped nuts.

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: In a large bowl combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry).
Reserving 2 cups crumb mixture; press remainder on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: sour cream enchilada casserole
directions: Combine water and 2 tablespoons picante sauce in a large shallow pan or dish.
Place tortillas in mixture and let stand 5 minutes; drain.
Cook ground beef and onion in a heavy skillet until brown.
Drain off excess grease.
Stir in salt, pepper, cumin, chili powder, garlic, olives and remaining picante sauce; simmer 5 minutes.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Pack in jars, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, nutmeg and salt together. Stir in the cold water.
Put on stove and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add lemon juice.
Pour hot syrup into jars, making sure there are no air holes.
Keep syrup hot while putting into jars. Process at 15 pounds pressure for 15 minutes.

title: red punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar. Add 1 quart of water and stir until blended.
Add rest of water, pineapple juice and 7-Up. Chill.

title: indian tacos
directions: Cook pinto beans and add Pace picante sauce or use 4 cans pinto beans.
Brown ground beef with garlic.
Don't chop.
Drain meat and remove garlic.
Add taco seasoning and tomato juice. Simmer 1 hour.
Chop lettuce, tomatoes,
and onion.
Grate 1 pound of Cheddar cheese.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Pound breasts between two sheets of Saran Wrap to 1/8-inch thickness.
Saute onion, green pepper, carrot and garlic in butter until soft.
Add bread crumbs and 1/2 cup broth to mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry surprise(frozen dessert)
directions: Mix together in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish flour, brown sugar, oleo and pecans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven, stirring often for 20 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Reserve 1 cup for topping. Spread the rest of the bottom of same dish evenly.

title: lemon-raspberry parfait
directions: In a saucepan, combine cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Mix together the milk and egg yolks and slowly stir into cornstarch mixture.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Boil, stirring, 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour through a sieve.
Whip the cream until it holds soft peaks.
Fold whipped cream into cooled pudding.
Halve pudding and fold raspberry puree into one half. Spoon alternating layers of pudding into parfait glasses. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Combine berries, 1 c. sugar, and 1/4 c. water in sauce pot on low heat until berries are soft - approximately 15 minutes. Combine corn starch and 3 Tbsp. water to berry mixture.
Cook until thickens.
Cool.

title: ribbon layered jello
directions: Dissolve 2 packages of gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add 1 cup boiling water and 1 can of milk.
Mix together and set mixture in warm water so it doesn't set.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup confectioners sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg in small bowl.
Set aside.
Combine milk, water, Crisco oil and lemon peel in medium saucepan.
Heat to rolling boil over medium-high heat.
Add flour mixture all at once.
Beat with wooden spoon until mixture pulls away from sides of pan into a ball. Remove from heat, cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Heat 2 to 3 inches Crisco oil in deep fryer or large saucepan to 350°.
Drop dough by tablespoon into hot Crisco oil.
Fry 3 or 4 puffs at a time 4 to 6 minutes, turning over several times.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.
Quick and easy dessert.

title: fruit juice cocktail
directions: Mix pineapple juice and almond flavoring. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: oven shrimp dish
directions: Use 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt cube of butter and add about 1/4 cup white wine and lots of garlic.
Add sliced mushrooms, onions and pieces of green and red peppers, pea pods and shrimp.
Cook at 350°, uncovered, turning shrimp once until done.
Serve over rice.

title: no oil dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in tightly covered container. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Shake before serving.
Makes about 3/4 cup dressing, 15 calories per serving.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except marshmallows, with electric mixer. Pour into buttered 1-quart casserole and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Sprinkle marshmallows on top shortly before removing dish from oven.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix melted margarine and brown sugar.
Cool slightly and add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add sifted flour to liquid mixture and mix well.
Add chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: prune, apple and chestnut stuffing for wild goose
directions: Soak prunes in wine overnight.
Remove the prunes, pit them and cut up in large pieces.
Pour the soaking liquid over the chestnuts in a small saucepan and add just enough water to barely cover them.
Simmer gently until the chestnuts are tender, about 25 minutes, and the liquid is nearly gone.
Stir in the butter, then mix together with the apple, prunes and the bread crumbs.
A touch of fresh rosemary is a good seasoner, but dried is apt to be too overpowering.
Makes 2 cups.

title: elaine's never fail cobbler
directions: Combine Bisquick, 1/2 cup sugar, milk and butter.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Scatter berries over batter. Combine water and 1 1/2 cups sugar in a saucepan and boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over berries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: goliath cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla and syrup. Add soda. Mix well. Then add peanut butter. Stir in oats, chips and M&M's. Mix well and drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Mix together lightly, stuffing, margarine and broth.
Spread half of mixture in buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix together chicken, celery, onion, mayonnaise and salt.
Spread over stuffing.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Mix together milk and eggs; pour slowly over top.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash fresh picked small cucumbers and pack in sterilized quart jars.
Add 1 clove garlic, 1 sprig fresh dill and 1/4 teaspoon mustard seed.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into casserole.
Top with grated cheese or cheese cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 8.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients together except flour.
Stir in 4 1/2 cups of flour or until a stiff mixture that you can pinch off and roll in a ball.
place on a cookie sheet.
Take a fork dipped in water and mash on the top of the cookie.
Bake at 350° until light brown, 9 minutes.
Makes lots of cookies.
Keep what dough you don't use in icebox and bake as needed.

title: chicken oriental
directions: In large skillet, brown onion in margarine.
Add chicken and cook until done.
Slice cabbage and add to chicken and onion.
Add Rice-A-Roni.
Cook until cabbage is done.
Serve while hot.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Soak bread in evaporated milk in bowl.
Add ground chuck, onion, egg, tomato sauce, salt and pepper; mix well. Shape into loaf.
Place in cast-iron baking pan.
Pour tomatoes over top. Bake, covered, at 400° for 1 hour.
Yield:
5 servings.

title: "lucky"
directions: Step 1:
Mix flour, margarine and chopped pecans.
Spread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let crust and pan cool.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cook until tender.
Drain, mix all other ingredients together and beat until "fluffy". Put in greased 9 x 13 pan or similar large dish. Cover and refrigerate.

title: sausage balls
directions: All ingredients at room temperature.
Mix until well blended. Make into balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until brown.

title: meringue puffs
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Line 2 cookie sheets with paper from paper grocery bags.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in a medium size bowl at high speed until peaks form.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating 1 to 2 minutes after each addition until mixture stands in stiff, glossy peaks.
Beat in vanilla. Spoon half of meringue mixture into decorating bag or plastic tube fitted with a large star shape.
Pipe into 1 1/4-inch star shapes on cookie sheets.
Repeat with remaining meringue.
Bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove from paper while meringues are still warm.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease and cool.
Chop into bite-size pieces the tomatoes and lettuce; chop onion and crush the taco chips.
Toss all ingredients and chill.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together and press into 8-inch spring-form pan.

title: pineapple, pecan cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, whip cream cheese until smooth.
Gently stir in pineapple, green peppers, green onions and seasonings.
Add American cheese (optional).
Turn out onto a sheet of plastic wrap and shape into a ball.
Roll cheese in nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: crisp onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In shallow baking pan, thoroughly blend all ingredients together, except potatoes and turn to coat thoroughly.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground meat; drain. Add pizza sauce to meat and heat through. Cut buns in half; top each with mixture, sliced pepperoni and shredded Mozzarella cheese. Put in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool.
Add 7-Up, sugar and vanilla.
Add nuts, if desired.
Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Cream and mix with crushed pineapple.
Mix into jello and pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill until set.

title: sweet dough
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 cup of the warm water.
Mix sugar, salt, shortening and yeast (which has been softened).
Add remaining 1/2 cup of water and the egg.
Add flours and mix well.
Knead on lightly floured board for 5 minutes.
Let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour).

title: philly cream cheese dip
directions: Beat all ingredients in small mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers or as a baked potato topper.

title: chili
directions: Fry out fat.
Cook chopped onions and garlic tender.
Add meat and cook until it loses its pinkish color.
Add 2 tablespoons flour.
Cook peppers with water and cook until tender.
Strain through strainer into meat.
Add tomatoes (well mashed), 1 quart of hot water and seasonings and cook for about 2 hours.
More hot water may be added, if needed.
Beans may be added. Cook chili at slow boil.

title: english stew
directions: In large saucepan layer cabbage (chopped), potatoes (diced), onion (rings) and cut sausage.
Add small amount of water.
Place on stove top.
Steam or boil until vegetables are tender.
Serve with corn bread.
Makes a nice meal for cold days.

title: crab mousse
directions: Combine celery, crabmeat, onion, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce in bowl.
Heat soup and cheese until warm, add wine and gelatine.
When gelatine is dissolved, add to crab mixture, mix and pour in lightly oiled mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.
